.

i don't know why i am avoiding my eyes in the mirror. i don't know why i fail to see what everyone sees. i don't hate myself. i'm still sane enough to know what things will push me over the edge. but still, whenever i try to tell myself a few words, i can't help but feel i am talking to a stranger. my mother is always annoyed whenever i deny a photo. she asks me why and i tell her i don't feel like it. but we both know that's not the case, we both know there's something else. and she keeps asking me, nevertheless. maybe hoping that i will change my mind. .
.
.

text:
"do you think", fragt teenager donna ihre beste freundin #laurapalmer, "that if you were falling in space, that you would slow down after a while, or go faster and faster?" "faster" antwortet laura. "faster and faster."
.
sie lebt ihr leben, zwischen #drogenrausch und #sexparties, dazwischen schule, aber auch ein brutaler überlebenskampf im haus ihrer eltern. denn ein geist lebt bei der familie, und er will besitz ergreifen von laura. in gestalt ihres vaters missbraucht bob, der geist, die junge frau seit jahren schon, als die handlung von #firewalkwithme beginnt.
.
bei seiner erstausstrahlung war #twinpeaks ein sittenstück, das lustvoll herzeigte, wie verdorben everybody's darling laura hinter ihrer unschuldigen teenager-fassade war. nach "fire walk with me" muss man lauras geschichte als eine gescheiterte #emanzipation lesen, die vor dem hintergrund von #metoo eine viel größere relevanz entfaltet, als der film noch in den 90ern hatte.
.
.
.
#emotionen #emotions  #achtsamkeit #kunst #art #aquarell #watercolor  #artoninstagram #nachdenken #film #filmkritik #serien #serienkritik #fernsehkritik

hvor lang tid tar et minutt?
for jeg tror ikke det tok
så mye mer.
kanskje ikke dét 
en gang.
men så mye jeg rakk å tenke.
eller ikke tenke.
utenfor min egen kropp
stod jeg handlingslammet 
og så på.
så på at kroppen min
ikke lenger var en kropp,
et menneske,
men en ting. 
kjente smerte
som jeg ikke fikk eie lenger.
falt bakover ut av tilværelsen
og inn 
i ingenting.
hjernen låste døren. - -

text:
nov 10 christian belton and i head to do the work of the lord.  i have spent an entire year planning and coordinating.  i heard a voice say launch this inaugural project in nigeria and i obeyed.  i have no corporate sponsors yet for this project but a few wonderful people have sowed into the vision.  however, the expenses far outweigh the donations but i trust god.  this project is about helping those who have been violated and hurt in such a way that’s unimaginable.  many survivors have never received counseling services.  many survivors feel they won’t be believed or heard so they stay quiet.  i care so much for each survivor.  i have been sent across the ocean to help.  i have been sent to say there is hope.  god has gifted me to teach. so me and a few others will train attendees on what best practices help women become restored. 
i am uber excited about the 8 interns coming from the university of abuja to volunteer as stars volunteer ambassadors.  each have been given a volunteer assignment and will also sit and be trained at the project.  i need to pay for their transportation to the training as we know many students don’t have lots of money. 
there are things that still need to be covered.  i am flying in a few young girls from a recovery house with the program director.  these young girls have been illicitly touched before.  that pains me.  we will encourage and celebrate them at the opening night gala. 
i need financial help getting them to abuja and back to lagos. 
sow a seed for a wonderful cause.  thank you in advance.  thank you to all who sowed already. 
www.tarinnaolley.com click donate #endsextrafficking #globalawareness #training #purpose #donationsneeded #metoo #ibelieveher #education #faith #survivors #counseling #mentalhealthawareness #trauma

text:
quite easily one of the most beautiful gifts i’ve ever been gifted.
i woke up in a pretty 
place + ready to train, but oh the mind chatter and anxiety was all the rage. don’t know why, because all is well but the monkey mind don’t care & will search endlessly when we allow it. 
who do you think you are? i’m so fat? why do i feel so big? i’m getting old. i used to be pretty.
on + on, if i let it, but not today my dark anxious friend.
not today. i got quiet and attempted to calm the chatter. 
108 times i said everything i am with an inhale and exhale. 
i am peace
i am calm
i am worthy
i am enough
i am beauty then who am i? what do i want? how can i serve?
and on & on then
i looked in the mirror and that’s all i saw, i closed my eyes
and that’s all i felt. 
i’ll prob have to do it again and again, but that’s the practice. i don’t think i’m alone here so i’d love to hear 
your chatter breaking practice. 
how do you get back to your light?
that chatter can 
never come between you and your path, because what it says has nothing to do with your light.#practiceandalliscoming 🍂
thank you for the beautiful gift @carbeans @maitrimalabeads there were plenty of #madurga chants in between all the i am’s, but this totally 
served me today🙏🏼
✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨
#iam #metoo #love #loveandalliscoming #yoga #yogaeverydamnday 
#itspractice #meditate #meditation #meditateeverydamnday #sheshines

text:
"as long as your needs are met"
today i want you to remember that you may not always get what you want or what you ask for sometimes but our god will forever supply your needs.  therefore we should be grateful.  many are worse off than you or wish they had access to what you have.  learn to appreciate & work with what you are already blessed with. 💖 #begrateful #livelaughlove #mentalhealth #metoo #survivor #blessed #jesuslovesme #blacklove #blackgirlmagic #blackpanther #laviniasmiles #kiss #laviniaspeaks #nolongeravictim #nolongerbound
name: Lavinia B. Masters

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

emmeline said make more noise, an artistic commentary video production from @catmonkeyrunning

the title emmeline said make more noise is in contrast to the meek shall inherit the earth tone of sylvia plath's (1932-'63) poem mushrooms (1960) which is generally interpreted as saying the oppressed will quietly rise up. emmeline pankhurst (1858-1928) said in her legendary speech of november 1913 you have to make more noise than anybody else. to be fair i should have included a photograph of every women alive and past, all deserve recognition

text:
a root of bitterness

hebrews 12:12-15

if you’ve ever tried to get rid of weeds in your lawn or garden, you know what a big problem they can be. you pull them out, and everything looks really good for a while, but before long, the unwanted growth returns because the roots are still there.
an unforgiving spirit is like a root branching out in all directions, affecting every area of our life. lopping off the leaves by repressing the pain and resentment isn’t a long-term solution, because like a weed, bitterness can continue to grow and reproduce as long as roots are in place.

when we’ve been deeply hurt, we sometimes resist offering forgiveness, thinking that a pardon excuses the wrongdoer and downplays the severity of the wrong done to us. but that’s not what forgiveness is—it’s letting go of both the offense and our right to demand payment, with the acknowledgment that vengeance is god’s responsibility, not ours (rom. 12:17-21). stubbornly refusing to forgive may seem like a way to get even, but it’s actually a poison that harms us. it hampers our ability to enjoy life and, like any sin, erodes our fellowship with the lord. unforgiveness could even affect our health, resulting in physical illness, anxiety, or depression.

but roots of bitterness don’t stop with us; they reach into our relationships, causing trouble and defiling others (heb. 12:15). an unforgiving spirit hinders our ability to love, poisoning the atmosphere in homes and workplaces.

isn’t it time to deal with that root of bitterness? lay down your grievances and refuse to rehearse your hurts. then fill your mind with positive things instead—namely, truths about the lord.
dr. charles stanley

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin

cnn

try to silence our brain,
we soak in the surroundings,
let ourselves breathe, 
the infinity of that moment, 
process the state of mind,

in the hope to find some answers,
we are afraid to counter.

text:
👏 new episode sponsored by @foundcoffeela: @aapiwomenlead: #imready 👏 (link in bio)
.
after coming back from a retreat for asian american women, i have fostered a deeper appreciation for physical spaces dedicated solely for asian women. that’s why  dr. connie wun (@seewun) is here today to share about her upcoming launch of #imready, being held from november 3rd-4th, 2018. she will be sharing how she founded her own organization for aapi women as the director of aapi women lead, “an intergenerational organization that strengthens the social and political power of aapi communities through the leadership of aapi women-identified, women and girls in solidarity with other communities of color.”
.
“the #imready movement aims to strengthen the progressive political and social platforms of asian and pacific islander communities in the us through the leadership of self-identified aapi women and girls.  our goal is to challenge and help end the intersections of violence against and within our communities. we do this work in solidarity with other communities of color.
.
the #imready movement raises visibility around self-identified aapi women and our experiences with #metoo, racial discrimination, war, immigration, and more. it also celebrates the leadership and power of aapi women in education, business, technology, and politics. at the conferences, we bring together aapi women leaders and our supporters to learn from one another, tell our stories, and to highlight our diverse leadership stories.
.
we invite you to join us to better understand the complex asian and pacific islander diasporas, histories, and experiences. we invite you to come honor the stories and leadership of our communities.
.
we are bringing together some of the most brilliant people to explore what it means to be a self-identified aapi woman in the united states. we know you are one of them.”
.
connie wun, ph.d., is co-founder of aapi women lead, a non-profit organization that helps to support the progressive social and political platforms of asian and pacific islander communities in the u.s through the leadership of self-identified women and girls.
.
avatar illustration by grace abe (@midorikoa)

сначала нужно сложить картину красочной фермы, потом расставить фигурки и можно приступать к веселой рыбалке. игра способствует развитию мышления, фантазии, логики, координации движений.

text:
promete que não vai crescer distante
promete que vai ser pra sempre assim
promete esse sorriso radiante
todas as vezes que você pensar em mim
promete cuidar bem dos seus cachinhos
e sempre me abraçar quando eu chegar
promete sorrir sempre com os olhinhos
e cantar cantigas na sala de estar
que eu prometo ser pra sempre o seu porto seguro
prometo dar-te eternamente o meu amor
promete aproveitar cada segundo
desse tempo que já passa tão veloz
me lembro quando você chegou nesse mundo
sorrindo aos poucos quando ouviu minha voz
e hoje corre pela sala, brinca de existir
giz de cera, pega-pega
e eu só sei sorrir
ao imaginar…
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
aktorja e famshme dhe shumë e dashur për publikun natalie portman ka zbuluar vështirësitë për të patur mikesha në hollywood.

së fundmi, ajo ka pozuar për revistën prestigjose “vanity fair” ku ka dhënë edhe një intervistë gjatë së cilës ka folur për karrierën e saj 20-vjeçare dhe marrëdhëniet me femra të tjera në industri.

ajo u shpreh se gjithmonë është ndjerë e vemtuar, me dëshirën për krijuar miqësi me vajza të tjera gjatë xhirimeve por jo vetëm. 37-vjeçarja ka rrëfyer se pas kaq shumë vitesh, falë lëvizjes kundër ngacmimeve seksuale “#metoo”, ka krijuar miqësi të vërteta që kurrë më parë nuk i ka patur. “jam afruar shumë me vajzat dhe gratë e industrisë. ne jemi mbledhur për të folur mbi ato çfarë ndodhin gjatë punës dhe karrierës sonë dhe shumë shpejt kuptova se nuk ishim kaq të panjohura për njëra-tjerën” ,-tha ajo.
name: City Radio Albania | City TV

.
in life, your self-belief will be under constant assault from the outside. - true growth, and the journey to unconditional self-acceptance, begins on the inside, though.
.
@themindshiftacademy i’ve walked through the fire. i’ve been emotionally burned, scarred and rebuilt from within. and now... i know my truth, i live my truth and i project my truth.
—> the result? people are magnetically drawn to my inner strength... like a moth to the flame.
.
realizing my true worth was like being born again. i felt transformed. recreated. alive.
.
i’ve now made it my mission to serve those of you are are tired.. stressed.. lost.. hurt.. emotionally burned.. scared.. fearful... .. there are proven steps, based on neuroscience, positive psychology, and emotional intelligence, that i took to fully transform myself. but it took me years of self-help to figure out the exact steps which triggered the most incredibly powerful shift of my life.
... i’ve put this together into an incredibly high impact, 12 week 1:1 coaching program called.. “build unbreakable self-belief” or b.u.s. 🚌 .
.
stop waiting for someone or something to heal you.. i’ll guide you through the steps to gain such insane clarity on who you are, what you stand for and what you are and are not willing to accept in your life that your mindset will be shifted forever.
.
👉click email above and reach out for a complimentary 20 mins discussion right now. it’s your time now. this is all about you 💕

are you ready to become your own greatest fan? .
.

text:
voice 
majlis' project for the month is based on the #metoo campaigning that has shaken the country awake. 
it is very evident that harassment and assault of all kinds have been prevalent all around us for ages, but why didn't we know? what stopped the victims from speaking up? what stopped them from sharing their stories? why didn't we hear their voice? 
voice is a series of posts on the several very real reasons why people didn't speak up as told to us by harassment survivors themselves. 
#voice #useyourvoice #useyourwords #voicemajlis
#metoo #metooindia

text:
cw: przemoc seksualna

tak wyglądam, kiedy kolejny raz pod postem zawierającym oskarżenie o gwałt czytam komentarz „ja go znam, on na pewno by tego nie zrobił”. uwaga, szok!: zdecydowana większość ludzi ma w życiu jakieś znajome osoby. to nie oznacza automatycznie, że nigdy nikomu nie zrobią krzywdy. tak, osoby stosujące przemoc też mają przyjaciół i przyjaciółki. 
gwałciciele to nie tylko ci, którzy po zmroku czyhają w ciemnej uliczce. wyobrażenie „gwałciciela idealnego” to mit – tak samo jak stereotyp „idealnej ofiary”. sprawcami i sprawczyniami przemocy często są osoby uwielbiane w towarzystwie, z dyplomami świetnych uczeni, mające „wzorowe rodziny”, mówiące „dzień dobry” i wspierające charytatywne zrzutki. 
wypowiedzi typu „chodziłem z nim do klasy, to dobry chłopak, na pewno jest niewinny” są szkodliwe i podważają wiarygodność osoby doświadczającej przemocy, która dzieli się swoją historią. 
jeśli mamy skończyć z kulturą gwałtu, musimy rozprawić się ze stereotypami – tak „idealnej” ofiary, jak i „idealnego” sprawcy. #metoo #stopkulturzegwałtu #endrapeculture #timesup

text:
robin wright llegó a intentar darle un cierre digno a @houseofcards, luego que la izquierda hollywoodense crucificara, sin tribunales, al actor y también productor #kevinspacey .

en 8 capítulos (no había manera de alargarla hasta 13), wright, quién también co-produce y dirige algunos episodios desde la segunda temporada, entrega a claire hare dispuesta a no enterrarse junto a su marido, quien la dejó, como “regalo” , a una poderosa y oligárquica familia  norteamericana, los sheperd, interpretados por diane lane (quien funciona a ratos) y greg kinnear… 
esta sexta temporada es prescindible, pero @netflixlat  nos tiene acostumbrados a crear productos adictivos que luego se desinflan al forzar nuevas temporadas (pienso en #bloodline y #sense8 , pero son más). claire hale es atacada en twitter, acosada por los hermanos sheperd (dueños de empresas químicas, de medios de comunicación y financistas de un tercer partido secreto que funciona como una logia tras el poder) y rechazada por los militares. con esas premisas incendiarias, el guion se decanta por mostrarnos lo cruel que es la política en dc, pero reducida a clichés y situaciones inverosímiles que no hay manera de conciliar. además, sigue la obsesión de darle un papel central al perro obediente doug stamper (michael kelly). la serie viaja al pasado con frecuencia para mostrarnos la relación juvenil de claire-annette e incluso amoríos de claire justo antes de escoger a frank. pero en esos recuerdos nunca aparece frank (spacey), ni siquiera escuchamos su voz en un momento crítico de la serie. la censura hollywoodense al máximo.

claire manipula todo lo que puede (es el espejo, distorsionado,  del fallecido frank underwood) y no le tiembla el pulso para ejecutar sin piedad.

hice la tarea, vi los ocho capítulos en formato maratón, pero al culminar sentí que el costo de oportunidad fue demasiado alto.

kevin, en un mundo post estupidez, post #metoo,  quizá puedas rehacer esa sexta temporada y hasta una séptima.

text:
what we talk about when we talk about rape by sohaila abdulali
genre - non-fiction, feminist 
style - honest, intelligent, conversational, many personal stories 
high point - abdulali’s work is powerful as she draws on her own harrowing experience, her work with 100s of survivors, she is unflinching, hopeful, defiant, proud, angry, and calls for healing in whatever form that might take for survivors, despite the horror she recalls she is ultimately uplifting 
low point - the many stories throughout her book reinforces enough is enough, we must keep talking, fighting, creating change 
take away - do not get comfortable, let’s talk, women are more than this experience

text:
so proud to be a #xoogler today. respect to the 20000+ #googlers who believed the stories of survivors instead of getting distracted by all the noise and planned the #googlewalkout. in my 4 years tenure in google and even post leaving google, i heard and witnessed such terrible incidents first hand where power hungry #googler and #xoogler predators just believed, they could get away with any kind of #harassment just because they were #google alums and that women had to "try it" cuz who cares about #consent. 
yes that's literally what an ex-google management level employee thought he could get away with even after leaving #google. the #groping, #pinching and absolute crassy behaviour happened right in front of my eyes to someone i care a lot for and it made me feel helpless and absolutely gutted that #she still had to be graceful about it cuz she didn't want it to hurt my career. kudos to her for being an absolute warrior and a true friend who chose to put my interests before her own safety. i finally did find my voice and threw him out of the room, but he still did not relent, throwing in the nonchalant "try it" #shamelessly before finally leaving. this #walkout needs to be a constant reminder to any past, present and future predators from #google. the #purge has begun and #googlers are clearly showing how they want to be remembered for inspiring employees around the world to stand up to sexual harassment. time is up! #google #googlers #timeisup #metoo #googlewalkout #inspirational #woke #inspired #united #xoogler #googler #consent #timesup #friendship #notokgoogle #dontbeevil

text:
-nä hörni tjejer nu är det dags att vi säger ifrån till patriarkatet och börjar kääämpa!!!
precis så skrek jag på det hjälmställdshetssymposium där jag fick tusen liter gratis bensin till min bmw suv om jag var med och verkade autentisk. en massa lantistanter med lila hår stod och luktade aco-salva och glufsade i sig mazariner precis när amelia adamo kom in och lyfte händerna och skrek: det finns inget fint väder, bara fina kläder! alltså, bara sååå sant! sedan fick jag några plastpåsar med lorean hudcreme och cliniquegrejer som plåster på moset för att verka tycka likadant. det var nog en plastsympåsium jag var på tänkte jag när alla sjöng kvinnliga internationalsången. lantistanterna blev påtvingade varsin livstidsprenumeration på amelia, skvalpade och skvätte på om att vi behöver fler mammskallar samt hötte med nävarna åt sega gubbarna därhemma. sedan blev tanterna hemskjutsade av sina äckliga själviska skitmän, utom jag som var bjuden på gratislunch på restaurang mångfaldiga mytomanen. det är så härligt att vara en sann idealist och hjälpa folk och vara nyttig! #amelia #kvinnokamp #metoo #halloween🎃 #medelålders #pumpa
name: Dagens Limerick

text:
thank you to everyone who came to my book launch in cookham last night at the media hub. it was one of the most poignant moments of my life and career.

i was blown away by the support i had from my close friends and family to the people i didn’t know, it was a really great friendly evening with such a warm energy emulating from the room. i couldn’t have asked for a better first night out on this.

speaking about my journey is never easy but it is the right thing for me to now do. i want my voice to give hope to others and give back opportunities for you to succeed.

don’t hold back is full of interactive activities and advice to improve your life, make you think differently, find new challenges and face your fears. if you’d like a signed copy i’ll be in henley next friday.

for more information on my book, signings or opportunities please email emmajanepa@gmail.com and speak with julie.

thank you to sarah parfitt for co-ordinating such a wonderful evening, my publisher naz ahsun, vision maker press for believing in me and to my production team, julie green, vivienne m clark, ross arrowsmith for guiding me with passion and talent!

i couldn’t be here without the support i get, so thank you to all from the bottom of my heart for being with me last night. 
enjoy your read 🙏🏼 💖 
www.emmajanetaylor.life

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the start.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing for the 2016 election.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are just helpless with the content and more or less fake accounts - there is no way they are going to risk their business by taking the responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole thing is build on the same user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

and here comes the best part. trumq is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words.

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

a non

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the start.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing for the 2016 election.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are just helpless with the content and more or less fake accounts - there is no way they are going to risk their business by taking the responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole thing is build on the same user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

and here comes the best part. trumq is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words.

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

a non

text:
marlina the murdererer in four acts (2017)
=====
first of all, i wanna say my biggest and deepest thank you to @mardian.reza (jakarta post contributor) for writing this amazing little article! so yeah just give this guy some love and help marlina to get nomination!

there’s a chance marlina will land a nomination and win the best foreign film category at the oscar—even defeating alfonso cuaron’s ‘roma’ which has become critics’ favorite. the members of the academy is known to be political and they might not watch all movoes submitted. they will most likely only watch and vote the films most people talk about. cinesurya has done everything to make ‘marlina’ relevant to the #metoo intiative which has become very hot topic of discussion at hollywood.

they even managed to sell the film through dvd which consists an interview about mouly surya talking the relevance between ‘marlina’ and #metoo movement. any movie telling story about gender equality needs to be watched and discussed, the problem is, ‘marlina’ has never been on the radar of hollywood's critics or film bloggers, such as indiewire and entertaintment weekly who have already predicted several foreign films to be nominated at the oscar ('marlina' is not one of them)

now is the moment to for us to make grassroot movement and popularaize #marlinagoestooscar by posting and writing everything on social media and tagging @theacademy to show that they should never not watch and not consider ‘marlina’ to be to be nominated. this is more than just a pride. this is a matter of a national identity and let the whole world knows who we are and what we can do.
=====
#reyzview
#gowatchitguys

text:
in 2014, steve bannon – then executive chairman of the “alt-right” news network breitbart – was christopher wylie’s boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analytica’s investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology – “information operations” – then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analytica’s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it’s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it’s like nixon on steroids.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
this #femalefounderfriday we're highlighting brazilian native daniela perdomo co-founded gotenna in 2012 with her brother, jorge, in brooklyn just after hurricane sandy tore through the eastern seaboard and knocked out power and cell service for thousands of people.

taking out nearly a quarter of all cell towers, the storm rendered communication virtually impossible at a very crucial time. “given we have supercomputers (phones) on us all the time, we decided that wasn’t acceptable,” perdomo, 32, recalled. “there needed to be a resilient phone-to-phone network that was people-powered, not dependent on large-scale solutions that fail us when we need them most.” gotenna creates decentralized connectivity through what it describes as the world’s first mobile, long-range mesh networks via peer-to-peer communications devices. it has two devices on the market, gotenna mesh and gotenna pro, both of which create independent mesh networks that let users send texts and share gps locations without cell service or wifi. the devices pair to regular phones as the interface.

the startup has raised a total of $16.8 million from investors such as union square ventures, walden venture capital, mentortech ventures, bloomberg beta, bbg ventures, and collaborative fund.

gotenna mesh is the company’s consumer device and began shipping mid-summer 2017. it has been adopted by more than 100,000 people and available in 42 countries, according to perdomo. each node acts as a relay for other devices, extending the range for everyone in the network.

like zatarain, perdomo – who grew up in sao paulo and moved to the u.s. when she was 18 – believes the latinx population is harder to quantify or identify because it comes “in literally every color.” “even our names don’t always clarify things,” she said. “latin america is a melting pot.” when it comes to being a minority co-founder, perdomo believes she probably gets discriminated against more due to her gender than her ethnic origin.

we love highlighting and celebrating our female founders who shatter the glass ceiling. 
#steam #stem  #tech #innovation #weareinnovators #timesup #metoo #weareinnovators #wwt2018 #wonderwomentech

gotenna mesh is the company’s consumer device and began shipping mid-summer 2017. it has been adopted by more than 100,000 people and available in 42 countries, according to perdomo. each node acts as a relay for other devices, extending the range for everyone in the network.

like zatarain, perdomo – who grew up in sao paulo and moved to the u.s. when she was 18 – believes the latinx population is harder to quantify or identify because it comes “in literally every color.” “even our names don’t always clarify things,” she said. “latin america is a melting pot.” when it comes to being a minority co-founder, perdomo believes she probably gets discriminated against more due to her gender than her ethnic origin.

we love highlighting and celebrating our female founders who shatter the glass ceiling.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower christopher wiley on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook (fb.o) users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
#움직씨 #두잉 #doing #북카페 #책방 
#페미니즘 #페미니즘북페어 #metoo #미투 .
.
🔫 두잉 페미니즘 북페어
🔫 doing feminism book fair 
강남역 10번출구 포스트잇 다양한 타자의 목소리와 쓰기가 그 강력한 소요를 만든 페미니즘 북카페 책방 두잉에서 나무연필 동녘 등 책들과 움직씨 출판사의 퀴어 페미니즘 책이 나란히 함께 나섭니다. 🙋🙋🙋🙋🙋
.
.
📍오늘 11.3(토) 14-20시
📍두잉 @doingfeminism 강남구 삼성로 654 b1
.
.
😎 두잉 페미니즘 북페어에 오시는 모든 분께 자기만의 목소리를 써내려 갈 흰 페이지「코끼리 가면」 미투 노트를 드립니다. .
.
😳 두잉 페미니즘 북페어에 코끼리 가면 초판본과 저자 사인본을 한정 수량으로 준비해 두겠습니다. .
.
😌 펀홈 레트로판과 방금 나와 퀵 배송된 펀홈 배지 2차 제작분을 만나실 수 있습니다.
.
.
😍 뉴 펀홈 사진을 찍어 주신 친구출판사 우드파크픽쳐북스 @woodpark_picturebooks 의 그래픽노블 「셀린 앤 엘라」도 두잉 북페어 움직씨 출판사 부스에서 함께 만나세요. .
.
🐘 여러 페미니스트들과 페미니즘 책을 만날 생각에 두근두근해요. 오늘 11월 3일 토요일 늦은 8시까지 열리는 두잉 페미니즘 북페어로 오세요 👵👵
.
.

강남역 10번출구 포스트잇 다양한 타자의 목소리와 쓰기가 그 강력한 소요를 만든 페미니즘 북카페 책방 두잉에서 나무연필 동녘 등 책들과 움직씨 출판사의 퀴어 페미니즘 책이 나란히 함께 나섭니다. 🙋🙋🙋🙋🙋
.
.
📍오늘 11.3(토) 14-20시
📍두잉  강남구 삼성로 654 b1
.
.
😎 두잉 페미니즘 북페어에 오시는 모든 분께 자기만의 목소리를 써내려 갈 흰 페이지「코끼리 가면」 미투 노트를 드립니다. .
.
😳 두잉 페미니즘 북페어에 코끼리 가면 초판본과 저자 사인본을 한정 수량으로 준비해 두겠습니다. .
.
😌 펀홈 레트로판과 방금 나와 퀵 배송된 펀홈 배지 2차 제작분을 만나실 수 있습니다.
.
.
😍 뉴 펀홈 사진을 찍어 주신 친구출판사 우드파크픽쳐북스  의 그래픽노블 「셀린 앤 엘라」도 두잉 북페어 움직씨 출판사 부스에서 함께 만나세요. .
.
🐘 여러 페미니스트들과 페미니즘 책을 만날 생각에 두근두근해요. 오늘 11월 3일 토요일 늦은 8시까지 열리는 두잉 페미니즘 북페어로 오세요 👵👵
.
.

#repost @dcastmusic with @get_repost
・・・
my grandma the feminist...
.
.
so i know it’s dia de los muertos💀and i know it’s a day to honor those who’ve passed and i love that and ❤️ 🙏🏾 my culture, but i just wanted to honor a special woman in my life while she’s still here.  my grandma.  she’s the only grandma i ever had growing up and she 💗s me 😊.
.
.
she’s lived a life...raised four children on her own, she’s always been tough as nails, she loves to drink beer (as you can see lol), makes some really great tamales, and she knows all the spots that i now go to in downtown la to hangout...cuz once upon a time she used to go to the same spots 😳.
.
.
she was never your typical abuelita (whatever that is 🤷🏽‍♂️)...but she’s always been strong, she’s super street-smart, loves to party, never let a man tell her what to do, and she literally, even to this day, does whatever she wants.  if that’s not feminism i don’t know what is 🤷🏽‍♂️.
.
. ✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨

.
.
.

text:
persephone’s rising molecular dancer

it's an odd experience creating a work i know will be around long after my grandchildren have come and gone... they are messages in bottles to the future cast towards a better more compassionate and inspired possibility, ... and combined with being present to the pressures of my current experience being feels all at once  gratifying and terrifying, perplexing and egotistical, defeated and hopeful (not all at once, mind you, but as waves of a great ocean upon the shores of my existence). corey allen reminded me recently that happiness is the smoke that rises from what's being done and what i am doing... it is not a goal or tangible object, only the wisps of the burning of being and the embers of doing. which sounds and feels like the buddhist's evocative description of forgiveness, the fragrance of the flower after it has been plucked or crushed.

text:
lord, we praise you for being faithful to us. lord we know that your name is above every name... even depression. we know that each person that is dealing with depression deals with it in a different way. we pray that you meet them at the point of their need. lord, you have the power to lift this depression off of the one suffering right now.  give them hope lord like only you can. help them to rely completely on your strength when they have none. regulate the chemicals in the brain that causes the sickness. lord, somebody needs you right now. they are desperately seeking complete and total healing. someone wants to smile, but can't. give them a reason to smile again. lord, please remove the hurt and the pain forever. mend their broken hearts. we know that there isn't one universal event that causes the onset of depression, so help us to show compassion and love to those who we know are dealing with this illness. lord, although we may not know all the signs of depression, nor can we always tell when someone is depressed, guide our feet to someone who may be dealing with it. give us a kind word to share that will help them go on. put someone in their path that will whisper a prayer for them, someone that will give them that hug that they need, someone that will sing a song that will tell touch their heart, or just a smile that will help them feel like they can make it. lord, we know that you are sovereign and you do all things well.  we thank you in advance for hearing our prayer and meeting our needs in the mighty name of jesus we pray. amen.
.
.
pray🙏🏾 |like❤️|share🌏
.
.

text:
it's not your fault, no matter what they say. it's not a survivor's fault and it's okay to take your time healing the wounds. it's okay to still have wounds that you could not get over. you and only you are the one who can decide what you should feel about your harassment, what step you wish to take and when you wish to speak up.

many brave women are speaking up about the abuse of their personal space and their consent and we admire their courage. it takes immense strength to speak up about sexual harassment and fuzia supports each survivor. 
if you wish to share your own story with the world, you can message us and we will publish it anonymously (or publicly if you wish to). we stand in solidarity with you, not and always.

___

text:
growing up i never really worried about any major social issues. i always felt safe, didn't see any injustices towards me for the fact of being a woman. but now that i've traveled so much, met so many people, and educated myself by reading i understand how this is not the case for every woman. not even all women in my own country. (this is just one more reason why i think euskadi is such a special place but i leave that for another post). the fact is that we are being assassinated, raped, abused and being thought of as less for our gender, and still have it denied in our faces. we see how judges question us instead of our agressors, because our skirt was too short or because we were out at night by ourselves. and my concern here is why are men not standing up against this with us? why are some women also denying these facts?
my answer is because of toxic masculinities. and because we, women of the world, are taught to compete against each other and love and take care of the men while they are allowed to have an accepting environment among themselves.
#metoo #niunamenos

text:
tuesday is the most consequential election in my lifetime so far. i'm going to be out of the country for the midterms so i made sure to get my mail-in ballot and sent it in today.
. . . . 
i believe the heart + soul of our country is at stake. we need to... stand up for racial + social justice. stand up for saving our planet. stand up for protecting our reproductive rights. stand up for caring for children being ripped apart from their families. stand up for human decency, kindness, compassion and empathy. stand up everyone's right to vote. . . . . 
which side of history do you want to be on? get to the polls on tuesday and do your civic duty. . . . . 
art via @ericcomstock . . . .

text_retweet:
#repost @savetheworldnowvegan with @get_repost
・・・
#repost  @earthlove777 rp @rod_veg_yves rp @gnarbivore rp @gnarbivore: "what's so bad about eggs?
🐣
the egg industry is one of the most inherently cruel of those in today's world of animal exploitation.
.
layer hens are kept in decrepit conditions, regardless of whether the carton states free range or organic! an inability to fluff and groom their feathers, extend their wings, scratch and graze and socialise drive the poor animals insane.
.
layer hens are selectively bred, genetically modified and manipulated into laying an unnatural amount of eggs compared to what they would naturally.
.
male chicks cannot lay eggs and are therefore considered a waste product. they are stuffed into plastic bags where they are left to suffocate or they are dropped into a macerator alive and turned into a pink pulp.
.
not to mention they are full of cholesterol and carcinogens!
. 
don't directly contribute to the murder and severe mistreatment of these poor, innocent beings. boycott eggs. be vegan. make the world a better place to live for all species that share the planet with us!

#dairyfree #dairy #govegan #eggs #freerange #organiceggs #egg #sunnysideup #scrambledeggs #poachedeggs #cheesecake #baconandeggs #cheesey #cheeseboard #creamy #cream #creamcheese #dairyisscary #stopseparatingfamilies #burgerking #tacobell #burrito #quesadilla #vegano #metoo #seperation #donttakeourplanetforgranted

text_retweet:
repost from @robynwilkerson - over decades of ministry i’ve counseled women who have dealt with various forms of sexual harassment. with the recent #metoo movement, the topic has become big news, and it is starting to get the attention it deserves.

let’s lay all of the cards out on the table. sexual harassment is one of those insidious evils that surround us. it lurks in the background and we don’t really pay much attention to it until it directly affects us in some way.

as women, we are often told we need to “move past” any “uncomfortable” situations we’ve experienced. as in the situation made us uncomfortable, but that’s the extent of it, giving the impression the woman is overreacting. all too often, sexual harassment is swept under the rug, or dealt with quietly so the situation just goes away.

i focus on two areas of this important topic in my newest blog post. first, i look a little closer at sexual harassment: what it is, who it affects, and what kind of damage it causes. then i look at the steps someone who is sexually harassed can take to find healing and how we can help.

read article at: robynwilkerson.com/findinghealing/
name: Ashley LeRoy Wilkerson

text: somebody told me they want to risk unconditional love because they’ve never known love without conditions before. 💕so let me ask this. 💕do you love yourself unconditionally? dare you fall wildly in love with the width of your hips? 🤸🏾‍♀️the kink of your hair? 💃🏿 the lover who left you? 💧the parents you’ve not yet made peace with? 🎎 could you risk pouring love over everything? 💕your response to every person, place and thing governs the ebb and flow of love in your life, either restricting or allowing 🥨 when you fall wildly in love with your own being i can’t say if you will magically draw romantic love  into your orbit...only destiny can say that...but you’ll definitely have a better chance of attracting someone who mirrors the delicious love you already feel and vibrate. and i guarantee 💯that (with or without a beloved) every morning that you wake up in your skin will be your homecoming🤸🏾‍♀️💫♥️ #radicalselflove #radicalfeminism #love #loved #loveislove #lovely #lovelymoments #loveme #spiritualawakening #spiritjunkie #spiritualgrowth #spirituality #thisisus #thisisme #spiritweek #metoo #metoomovement #womenempowerment #womenempoweringwomen #spiritualrevolution #spiritualwarrior #radicalselfcare  #loveyourself #love #loveislove #lovely #loveher #loveislove #loveyou

text:
#donaldtrump told former lawyer #michaelcohen that 'black people are too stupid to vote for me' .
.
.
.
trump’s former lawyer says the ex-reality tv star frequently made offensive and racist comments in private — even telling him during the 2016 campaign he believed “black people are too stupid to vote for me.” michael cohen told vanity fair on friday that he often heard trump make such comments behind closed doors. 
cohen recounted a discussion he had with the then-presidential candidate at trump tower in 2016 in which the one-time trump confidante noted that the crowd at a rally earlier in the day was largely caucasian.
“i told trump that the rally looked vanilla on television. trump responded, ‘that’s because black people are too stupid to vote for me,’” cohen told the magazine.

years earlier, shortly after the death of nelson mandela, cohen claims that trump asked him to, “name one country run by a black person that’s not a s---hole,” adding, “name one city.”
“i’m not surprised at all,” a source with ties to the white house told the daily news. “so many people have come forward with similar stories.” cohen also recalled a trip in the 2000s in which he and trump were riding in a car riding through a run-down neighborhood in chicago on the way to a business meeting. trump took note of his surroundings and said something to the effect of “only the blacks could live like this.” another racist comment came from trump when the pair were discussing past seasons of “the apprentice.” the two were talking about the show’s first season, which ended with two contestants, bill rancic and kwame jackson, in a head-to-head.
“trump was explaining his back-and-forth about not picking jackson,” an african-american investment manager who had graduated from harvard business school, cohen said. “he said, ‘there’s no way i can let this black f-g win.’” stay focused! don’t get discouraged, get mad, fight harder & smarter than republicans, get even! go vote and take 5 people with you. #votolatino #rockthevote #democrats #midterms #bluewave  #blacklivesmatter #blackgirlsrock #voterregistration #voting  #votingday #metoo #women #trump #racism  #votersuppression #vote #voteblue

text:
thousands of google employees walked out during work hours at campuses all over the world thursday to protest how the company deals with sexual harassment.
google was our last hope. a tech company that could provide services now plus a positive vision of the future.
apple™️ can’t be that. it’s a company that overcharges for products so that you can join their lifestyle brand/cult. 
microsoft®️ can’t be that. they charge people for a sub-par windows 10 experience so that they can spy on you and sell your data.
google was different. google had a really good motto: don’t be evil.
but they got rid of that motto. they ditched the idea that a giant corporation hoovering up personal data shouldn’t be evil because greed is evil. and they wanted to be greedy.
that’s caused all of their morals to go down the drain. what do we do about that? how do we fix google? how do we make it a beacon for mankind. #google #walkout #metoo #apple #microsoft #dontbeevil

text:
bollywood's #metoo reckoning: 'we #thought it would take 20 more years' - in #images ⠀
introducing the recent series opener of india’s top-rated talk show, koffee with karan, the director-producer-personality karan johar championed bollywood’s new-found “girl power”: 12 months of successes – such as the taut spy thriller raazi and the raucous bridal comedy veere di wedding – that were led and authored by women. his guests, accordingly, were distaff royalty: reigning queen deepika padukone, newly radiant after surviving january’s trial-by-fire film padmaavat, and beaming princess alia bhatt, raazi’s immensely talented young lead. reclined on johar’s nortonesque couch, bhatt was offered a cuddly sophie’s choice between her much-instagrammed cats and beau ranbir kapoor; padukone raised a suggestive eyebrow after asked what she first notices in a man.⠀
if the show’s peppy tone was enjoyable, it felt strangely removed from the grim claims emerging on social media from women occupying the film industry’s lower ranks. india’s #metoo movement – initiated in early october and gathering rapid pace... see more: https://londonuk.news/article?id=959

text:
querida amiga, en este día, tu día te pedimos para que de nuestros cuerpos se aleje la cultura psicópata de los piquetitos. que florezcan mis flores en nuestra tierra latinoamericanas, más cantos, más arte, mas vida, que más mujeres artistas puedan ser visibilizadas en las calles, los teatros, las galerías y los museos. qué la prensa y la crítica empiece a escribir sus páginas, que la historia del arte las considere, que los galeristas las expongan, que los coleccionistas se enamoren. que la vida sea más linda y mas justa para nosotras también en cada gesto. para que la esclavitud no se establezca nunca mas como bandera entre las mujeres tampoco y que vivamos en una latinoamerica más justa y con igualdad. gracias #fridakalho #hermana, #madre y #amiga! hersilia alvarez, 2 de noviembre de 2018.

text:
querida amiga, en este día, tu día te pedimos para que de nuestros cuerpos se aleje la cultura psicópata de los piquetitos. que florezcan mis flores en nuestra tierra latinoamericanas, más cantos, más arte, mas vida, que más mujeres artistas puedan ser visibilizadas en las calles, los teatros, las galerías y los museos. qué la prensa y la crítica empiece a escribir sus páginas, que la historia del arte las considere, que los galeristas las expongan, que los coleccionistas se enamoren. que la vida sea más linda y mas justa para nosotras también en cada gesto. para que la esclavitud no se establezca nunca mas como bandera sobre nuestros cuerpos y que vivamos en una latinoamerica más justa e igualitaria.  gracias #fridakalho #hermana, #madre y #amiga!

hersilia alvarez, 2 de noviembre de 2018.

text: @google’s chief executive, @sundarpichai, issued a mea culpa of sorts as its employees around the world held walkouts to protest how the company had handled sexual harassment. “it’s been a difficult time here,” he said thursday at the @nytimes dealbook conference. “at google, we set a very high bar, and we clearly didn’t live up to our expectations.” the company gave male executives millions of dollars in exit packages after they were accused of sexual misconduct, according to an article in @nytimes last week. sundar told @sorkinsays that google has “drawn a very hard line” on inappropriate behavior in recent years and that the company is now “a different place.” he said that “there are concrete steps coming up” as the company grapples with their own #metoo moment. sundar was photographed by @mikecohenphotography at @jazzdotorg. visit the link in our profile to see more.

text:
this holiday season, remember, everyone's abuser has not moved on and is not just accepting things as they are. things are tough on them as well, they may have a family that they may feel has been broken up. they will act out because that is their nature. create a safety word if you feel endangered or plain ole sad. allow a few people around you to know that word or phrase so they can spring into action. create a plan for when the word is said. it is as simple as saying, "wow, this sweater is itchy" or "i do not like pumpkin pie". the plan is to keep you and everyone around safe. create it based on something that you don't like or something simple, but create it so you can get support you need. don't suffer in silence this year.

text:
today is hard. november 2nd has been hard for the past few years. november 2nd, 2018 marks 4 years since my rape. 4 years of strength, advocacy, activism, courage, and survival.
.
.
.
4 years ago, i had no idea that i would be a voice in what is now the #metoo movement. 4 years ago, my life changed. here’s to changing the culture of rape, putting an end to victim blaming, and to believing survivors. .
.
. “i survived because the fire inside me burned brighter than the fire around me.”
.
.
.
.
#nomore1in4 #autumnagainstassault #missil19

text: what is the cage that surrounds you and keeps you from lifting off into freedom? often times freeing yourself from that cage is a challenging and courageous journey. if you are on that journey, remember that you are still allowed to sing your song, to express your voice, your life. sometimes that may be a song of hope, other times a song of sorrow. your song matters and you have a right to sing. you don’t have to wait to start living. i want you to have as much freedom as possible and your life is valuable and beautiful whether you’re still encaged in a battle for freedom or soaring high in victory. either place, and everywhere in-between, sing. #therecoverycorner #womenempowerment #metoo #metoomovement #seattlewomen #seattletherapygroup #seattletherapy

text: welp. were not friends.....if ur not voting on november 6th.............. if you think your vote does not matter or that these issues do not pertain to you or that im being dramatic you are just wrong. this election directly effects everyone and everyone should be concerned. at least two years of unrestricted trump bills!!! unrestricted oppression of all marginalized groups that will pass through congress!!! you really dont care that he is killing millions of people and our planet??? if you cannot see that our present day government is a result of all events that happened since slavery and civil rights (only like 60 years ago) and that no joke the same people have been in office for 50+ years because there are no term limits for senate, hr and supreme court. yes. really. research jamie whitten, john dingell, robert byrd and sooo many more. they stayed in office for 50+ years and a lot of them voted no on the civil rights act and voting rights act that gave black people the right to vote and had a say in our laws well into the 2000’s!!!!! yes some democrats are corrupt and greedy. but so is our whole government that was built off of racism and suppression where all those old white people (~80% white) let me repeat 80 percent white in congress have been there for decades deciding who can and cant have rights and where all the money goes. these corrupt old rich white people with old bigoted views want you not to vote so they can keep their long-standing power. they dont teach systems of oppression in school for a reason! our government decides what is taught and ignorance=complacency! everything they are doing rn is destructive. it is a slow process yes, but not contributing is basically a vote for the other side. a vote for complacency and white supremacy. isnt the logic pretty clear here??? if you have read this far thank you and i hope you can think about your position and amount of privilege you have or dont have in our world and recognize that this is an opportunity to help your family/ your own standing towards equality and the equality of others who you may have innately benefited off of because of history. so use the only power you are given and vote blue.

text:
there are a lot of reasons rape victims don’t speak up or report their experience to the police. until you are in the same position you shouldn’t judge or shame them for not telling anyone. period. just imagine how they feel. having empathy is one step closer to showing your support. we need to listen to their stories and go from there.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
my new project, our stories matter, is a way for everyone to be heard. victims of assault, abuse, rape, and domestic violence have voices and we need to listen and support them. i’ve also teamed up with licensed psychotherapist @cosmicchristine to help provide a safe place for people to come forward and open up.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
we are currently accepting submissions for the project. sharing your story not only can be therapeutic, but can help others with healing. and you can be anonymous if it makes you more comfortable. this collaborative journal will be real, raw, eye-opening, heartbreaking, and inspirational. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
you can learn more at ourstoriesmatter.info
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
so, i was minding my own business, eating lunch today when bishop don juan showed up. 
i couldn't help but think about his every day life. 
in the day and age of #metoo, i hope every day for him is like the scene from i'm gonna git you sucka when everyone was clowning fly guy when he got out of jail.

it's almost 2019, dude. being a cliche that represents beating and exploiting women isn't cool.

some d-bag bought him lunch and i used that opportunity to hijack the photo opp he paid for.

text:
อัยการแอลเอ ไม่ฟ้อง “สไล” ลวนลามหญิง

เมื่อวันที่ 30 ตุลาคม 2018 สำนักงานอัยการของแอลเอ เคาน์ตี้ แถลงปฏิเสธข่าวการตั้งข้อหาดารานักบู๊ ซิลเวสเตร์ สตัลโลน วัย 72 ปี ในข้อหาเกี่ยวกับการรังแกทางเพศ ตามข่าวที่ปรากฎออกมาก่อนหน้านั้น โดยบอกว่าพยานในคดีนี้ไม่สามารถให้การยืนยันได้ว่า ดาราที่สร้างชื่อจากบท “ร็อคกี้” และ “แรมโบ้” เคยมีพฤติกรรมเข้าข่ายลวนลามทางเพศ เมื่อปี 1987 และ 1990 จริงตามข้อกล่าวหา

สำนักงานอัยการยังบอกด้วยว่า ข้อหากล่าวหาดังกล่าว ถือว่าหมดอายุความแล้วตามกฎหมาย

นอกจากนี้ สำนักงานอัยการของแอลเอ เคาน์ตี้ ยังบอกด้วยว่า สตรีที่อ้างตัวเป็นเหยื่อของ ซิลเวสเตอร์ สตัลโลน คนดังกล่าว มีสัมพันธ์แบบเปิดเผยกับนักแสดงหนุ่มเป็นเวลาหลายปี ก่อนที่สัมพันธ์ของทั้งสองจะยุติลงในภายหลัง

ข่าวบอกว่าข้อกล่าวหาดังกล่าว ปรากฎเป็นข่าวขึ้นเมื่อเดือนมิถุนายนที่ผ่านมา ท่ามกลางกระแส #metoo ที่มีการฟ้องร้องเอาผิดนักแสดง หรือผู้สร้างภาพยนตร์หลายราย รวมไปถึงนักการเมือง และบุคคลอีกหลายสาขาวิชาชีพ.

นอกจากนี้ สำนักงานอัยการของแอลเอ เคาน์ตี้ ยังบอกด้วยว่า สตรีที่อ้างตัวเป็นเหยื่อของ ซิลเวสเตอร์ สตัลโลน คนดังกล่าว มีสัมพันธ์แบบเปิดเผยกับนักแสดงหนุ่มเป็นเวลาหลายปี ก่อนที่สัมพันธ์ของทั้งสองจะยุติลงในภายหลัง

ข่าวบอกว่าข้อกล่าวหาดังกล่าว ปรากฎเป็นข่าวขึ้นเมื่อเดือนมิถุนายนที่ผ่านมา ท่ามกลางกระแส #metoo ที่มีการฟ้องร้องเอาผิดนักแสดง หรือผู้สร้างภาพยนตร์หลายราย รวมไปถึงนักการเมือง และบุคคลอีกหลายสาขาวิชาชีพ.

text:
los dominicanos suscritos a los servicios de netflix ya tienen disponible desde este viernes la sexta y última temporada de la icónica serie hause of card que ahora tendrá como presidenta a claire underwood, que inicia como viuda de un francis underwood cuya muerte no fue plasmada en la producción.

el espíritu de francis underwood y sus fechorías del pasado persiguen la sexta temporada de “house of cards” y a su nueva presidenta estadounidense, la viuda claire underwood.

francis está muerto, como deja claro una imagen de claire tiernamente inclinada sobre su ataúd.

pero ni los productores ni el elenco sugieren que la muerte de underwood _ tras el despido del astro kevin spacey desatado por #metoo _ le haya pasado factura a la historia de esta sátira política. la trama sigue el camino al ascenso de claire al cual se hizo referencia al final de la quinta temporada, pese a la agitación que paralizó la producción hace un año cuando spacy fue acusado de conducta sexual inapropiada. “básicamente, la única respuesta que podíamos tener fue la que tuvimos”, dijo el productor frank pugliese. “que es que el elenco y el equipo y todos los involucrados decidieron inclinar la cabeza y responder contando la mejor historia que nos era posible. era la única manera en que podíamos responder a cualquier cosa, cualquier circunstancia”. robin wright, ahora sola como claire, dice que recuperarse tras la salida de spacey y su personaje requirió de un esfuerzo grupal. “todos realmente colaboramos y queríamos lo mejor para la serie. así que pienso que fue una reunión de, ‘vamos, salgamos adelante y sigamos’”, dijo la actriz, quien declinó hacer comentarios sobre si spacey fue echado de menos en el plató.

cuando el estudio aprobó la reanudación del programa sin él, evitó dejar inconcluso el drama que puso a netflix en el mapa como un destino de programación original. “house of cards” también pregonó el auge de otras plataformas de streaming y programas aclamados, incluyendo “the handmaid’s tale” de hulu.

el que francis muriera pero no fuera olvidado era inevitable, dijo pugliese.

text:
3/5 📷📖
—varias serias exitosas, como “wanderlust” o “la casa de las flores”, desde un ángulo más light están analizando los patrones morales con cierto ánimo de revisar lo que antes se consideraban fetiches.
—sí. el lado más oscuro del sexo está muy abierto al debate. lo cual me parece muy bien, porque las líneas que separan lo bueno de lo malo son muy delgaditas. y esos, justamente, son el tipo de personajes, que me interesan: los que tienen varias capas, que te permiten explorar la naturaleza humana y las relaciones. nicole kidman [en bll] es un personaje cargado de misterio, que está siempre al límite de miles de sentimientos.
—sé que estás participando de una serie de foros de empoderamiento, en los ángeles.
sí, son unos eventos con paneles y diálogos dirigidos a mujeres, hombres y personas transgénero.un panel, por ejemplo,se dio con un grupo de mujeres que representan a las agricultoras latinas, que se unieron para enviarle una carta a donald trump, y se publicó en “time magazine”.su discurso no es el de la queja, ni la victimización. intentan explicar su rol en la comunidad,cuentan cómo nos proporcionan alimentos, cuánto ganan y, encima,cómo las tratan por ser inmigrantes.
—¿alguna vez sentiste prejuicios por ser una actriz latina en hollywood?
—siento que los directores y los escritores todavía tienen una idea de la latina como una mujer sumisa y plana. hace un tiempo publiqué un tweet que decía “you are too beautiful for this role”, que fue algo que me dijeron cuando fui a un casting para el papel de una mujer latina. nos tienen encasilladas. no nos dan un papel fuerte, de una empresaria, de alguien de éxito… nos ponen de la esposa del narco, o en el de la persona de la limpieza.
—¿qué se puede hacer para cambiar esto?
—yo estoy buscando papeles fuertes. se lo he dicho a mis agentes y mis representantes. no quiero algo que solamente se base en una relación amorosa frustrada entre los protagonistas, que siempre acaba en melodrama.
—¿esto está cambiando con #metoo?
—sí, eso sí ha tenido impacto. por eso son tan importantes estos movimientos. y yo misma quiero ser un vehículo de comunicación y de cambio.

text:
los dominicanos suscritos a los servicios de netflix ya tienen disponible desde este viernes la sexta y última temporada de la icónica serie hause of card que ahora tendrá como presidenta a claire underwood, que inicia como viuda de un francis underwood cuya muerte no fue plasmada en la producción.

el espíritu de francis underwood y sus fechorías del pasado persiguen la sexta temporada de “house of cards” y a su nueva presidenta estadounidense, la viuda claire underwood.

francis está muerto, como deja claro una imagen de claire tiernamente inclinada sobre su ataúd.

pero ni los productores ni el elenco sugieren que la muerte de underwood _ tras el despido del astro kevin spacey desatado por #metoo _ le haya pasado factura a la historia de esta sátira política. la trama sigue el camino al ascenso de claire al cual se hizo referencia al final de la quinta temporada, pese a la agitación que paralizó la producción hace un año cuando spacy fue acusado de conducta sexual inapropiada. “básicamente, la única respuesta que podíamos tener fue la que tuvimos”, dijo el productor frank pugliese. “que es que el elenco y el equipo y todos los involucrados decidieron inclinar la cabeza y responder contando la mejor historia que nos era posible. era la única manera en que podíamos responder a cualquier cosa, cualquier circunstancia”. robin wright, ahora sola como claire, dice que recuperarse tras la salida de spacey y su personaje requirió de un esfuerzo grupal. “todos realmente colaboramos y queríamos lo mejor para la serie. así que pienso que fue una reunión de, ‘vamos, salgamos adelante y sigamos’”, dijo la actriz, quien declinó hacer comentarios sobre si spacey fue echado de menos en el plató.

cuando el estudio aprobó la reanudación del programa sin él, evitó dejar inconcluso el drama que puso a netflix en el mapa como un destino de programación original. “house of cards” también pregonó el auge de otras plataformas de streaming y programas aclamados, incluyendo “the handmaid’s tale” de hulu.

el que francis muriera pero no fuera olvidado era inevitable, dijo pugliese.

hulu . el que francis muriera pero fuera olvidado era inevitable , dijo pugliese .

text:
#metoo. #niunamenos. #googleprotectssexualpredators. 🙏🏽🌀🙏🏽🌀🙏🏽🌀🙏🏽🌀🙏🏽
all employees and contract workers across the company deserve to be safe. sadly, the executive team has demonstrated through their lack of meaningful action that our safety is not a priority. we’ve waited for #leadership to fix these problems, but have come to this conclusion: no one is going to do it for us. so we are here, standing #together, protecting and supporting each other. we demand an end to the sexual #harassment, #discrimination, and the systemic #racism that fuel this destructive culture.

we are building on the work of others. many at #google have been advocating for structural change for years. it’s their legacy and leadership that made this moment possible. we are a small part of a massive movement that has been growing for a long time. we are inspired by everyone from the women in fast food who led an action against sexual harassment to the thousands of women in the #metoo movement who have been the beginning of the end for this type of abuse.

so today, over 60 percent of all google offices, and thousands of google employees will walk out, around the world.

all employees protesting today are united in calling for these changes:

an end to forced #arbitration in cases of harassment and discrimination for all #current and #future employees, along with a right for every google worker to bring a co-worker, representative, or supporter of their choosing when meeting with #hr, especially when filing a harassment claim.... #reparations

text:
the ever-so-amazing bartender – pippa guy – who’s added a fierce energy, grace and softness to the award-winning american bar at the savoy hotel.
.
we’re just getting to know pippa – we’ve met a couple of times. pippa is just heading into her 6th year as a bartender, and she firmly believes that “you get out what you put in – there are so many people that work incredibly hard, but there’s not enough support and appreciation towards everyone’s dedication.” over the next three years, pippa hopes to see the industry become even more conscious of our impact on the environment. she’s hoping that each of us will take more of a leading role in this cause – how do we look after “waste”, what is “waste” and how do we manage the world around us? .
.
when it comes to the drinks industry, and when it comes to making a difference, pippa’s advice is simple “stop doubting yourself”. pippa’s journey at the savoy is ear marked by a figure she would love to chat with – ada coleman – the first and only female head bartender at the american bar. “from the records we have, ada seems to be a pretty fiery character, but also took quite a lot of unpleasant treatment in her position. i’d love to buy her a martini and listen to her stories. she’s ultra-inspiring.” .
beyond the savoy, pippa desperately wants to spend some time in california – after all, her mum was born there, and craves some family and beach time! if pippa wasn’t bartending, she’d most likely something to do within the science, sport or travel industries; “i’ve always thought i’d really enjoy marine biology, the problem is, i’d be awful at sitting behind a desk for long periods of time – how can people get anything done sitting in one spot for so long?!” the perfect moment for a cocktail? “i’m a complete sun worshiper, so after a long day in the sun, just towards sunset, somewhere outside with a good view, i’m drinking a gin & tonic.” .
.
pippa’s one line that describes her, “there is freedom waiting for you, on the breezes of the sky, and you ask ‘what if i fall?’ oh but my darling, what if you fly?” wise words from erin hanson. 
#minibarleadingladies
name: Drinks Industry Women/Fem Folx

when it comes to the drinks industry, and when it comes to making a difference, pippa’s advice is simple “stop doubting yourself”. pippa’s journey at the savoy is ear marked by a figure she would love to chat with – ada coleman – the first and only female head bartender at the american bar. “from the records we have, ada seems to be a pretty fiery character, but also took quite a lot of unpleasant treatment in her position. i’d love to buy her a martini and listen to her stories. she’s ultra-inspiring.” .
beyond the savoy, pippa desperately wants to spend some time in california – after all, her mum was born there, and craves some family and beach time! if pippa wasn’t bartending, she’d most likely something to do within the science, sport or travel industries; “i’ve always thought i’d really enjoy marine biology, the problem is, i’d be awful at sitting behind a desk for long periods of time – how can people get anything done sitting in one spot for so long?!” the perfect moment for a cocktail? “i’m a complete sun worshiper, so after a long day in the sun, just towards sunset, somewhere outside with a good view, i’m drinking a gin & tonic.” .
.
pippa’s one line that describes her, “there is freedom waiting for you, on the breezes of the sky, and you ask ‘what if i fall?’ oh but my darling, what if you fly?” wise words from erin hanson.
