text:
heading south of the border, let’s chat to rebekkah dooley – in new york, ny. “i’ve been working in the f&b industry since i was 16.” after rebekkah skipped college, she found herself working in marketing, pr and events within the hospitality industry – landing at the award-winning dead rabbit grocery & grog in nyc. “working at the dead rabbit as their marketing & pr director is my dream job!” remarking on how much she’s always wanted to be part of the team. “it's so rewarding to work with such a strong, kick-ass female team - being surrounded by women who excel at what they do inspires me so much, and makes me want be better everyday. we have support, and we have each other’s backs.” .
.
rebekkah is hoping for more opportunities for this network of female bartenders to spend a bit more of their privilege, and open bars – build something to own. she struggles to name more than a couple examples from her london home town, and is concerned not just on the reality, but what steps we can take to change this – how can we empower more women into ownership? .
.
while reflecting on her past, she talks about her father – who passed away from alcohol abuse when rebbekah was 13. this is a big part of why she works in the beverage industry – helping to present better habits, lifestyle changes, treating premium cocktails as a privilege, while educating bartenders at all levels on their responsibilities to the public. it’s no surprise that rebekkah wanted to be a teacher – especially coming from a family of all teachers – with her attitude towards the industry. today, teaching isn’t an academic post-graduate for rebekkah, instead she’s developing her own way of teaching in the drinks industry, and it’s inspiring several people.
.
.
her advice? be proud of what you do, every day. if you can't take pride in what you're doing, you probably shouldn't be doing it, and to her 16 year old self, “that boy isn’t worth it”. #minibarleadingladies

text:
the other day, i asked my boyfriend, “what’s my worst quality?” i’ve been working on bettering myself lately, and i knew he’d give me an honest answer. i assumed he’d say that i was impatient or that i would talk over him too much. his answered surprised me. he said, “you doubt yourself too much.” i knew he was right, but i never thought it was my worst quality. he reminded me even though i am doing well at my new job and how i successfully run her every day, i still don’t believe in myself. i doubt that what i’m doing with her is impactful for others. i doubt that my efforts for her are good enough. i doubt my abilities and worry that i’m not doing well enough at work. i even doubt my relationships with friends and family. and truth be told, if i had a friend who was like me, i would probably think she’s pretty badass. but because it’s me, i always compare myself to others and only see my flaws. .
why is this? often, survivors who have been manipulated, controlled, or gaslighted, tend to lose trust in themselves. the pressure to be perfect for our abusers (which is self-imposed after the abuse) is a lingering effect of trauma. .
so how do we heal from that? i need to remind myself every day that i am good enough, that i belong, and that i am deserving. my boyfriend recently told my best friend this same thing the other night. she’s such a talented artist, but i don’t know that she sees it. i’m hoping if we all tell her enough times, she’ll really understand that her work is visionary and her ideas matter. and i know that if i can say all those things about my best friend, i can say them about myself. so here’s my mantra: i am deserving of the love i give to others.
.
i know becoming a confident woman won’t happen overnight. but i’m surrounding myself with people who reinforce my mantra. i want to be surrounded by friends and family who believe in me too. so if you’re struggling with these same doubts, dm me. we could all use more friends who uplift us. and i’d love to be that for you. 💜💙 #weareher

text:
❌
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ wie gerne hätte ich als kind schon gelesen:
„du bist nicht allein, du darfst fliehen, dir wird geholfen.“ oder: „𝐃𝐄𝐈𝐍 𝐊𝐎̈𝐑𝐏𝐄𝐑 𝐮𝐧𝐝 𝐃𝐄𝐈𝐍𝐄 𝐒𝐄𝐗𝐔𝐀𝐋𝐈𝐓𝐀̈𝐓 𝐆𝐄𝐇𝐎̈𝐑𝐓 𝐍𝐔𝐑 𝐃𝐈𝐑 𝐚𝐥𝐥𝐞𝐢𝐧! 
𝐃𝐮 𝐡𝐚𝐬𝐭 𝐣𝐞𝐝𝐞𝐬 𝐑𝐄𝐂𝐇𝐓 𝐚𝐮𝐟 𝐞𝐢𝐧 „𝐍𝐄𝐈𝐍“!“ dieses jahr feier ich, dass ich nun die hälfte meines lebens 𝐟𝐫𝐞𝐢 sein darf. 
14 jahre lang befand ich mich jedoch in „obhut“ eines käfigs,
dessen schmied und einziger wächter mein vater war.
er bestimmte über meine sexualität, kontrollierte mein leben. 
er machte mir geschenke, als er merkte, dass ich langsam realisierte (und vorher mit ekel ahnte), dass es falsch u. verboten war, was er mir antat. es schien, als glaubte er, mich bestechen zu können- als ob ich je die wahl gehabt hätte.
wenn ich die letzten reste mut zusammenkratzte, um ihn zu sagen, dass ich es nicht mehr ertragen könne, schlug er mich, drängte mich in eine zimmerecke, bäumte sich vor mir auf und beschimpfe mich. 
er krönte mich zu seiner „mitverantwortlichen“. warum ich nicht schon früher weglief? welches kind möchte/kann die verantwortung tragen, die famile auseinander zu reißen oder der mutter zu be(r)ichten, dass ihr ehemann die gemeinsame tochter zu seiner versklavten affäre macht? 
letztendlich entschied ich, mich aus seiner gewalt zu reißen: mit 14 rannte ich weg, zur polizei, sagte aus, lies eine anzeige gegen ihn erstatten. 
weshalb ich diese zeilen dem internet zugänglich mache? 
vielleicht hätte ich mich eher von meinem vater befreien können, hätte ich zugriff auf informationen gehabt, dass und wo ich mir hilfe holen und mich austauschen kann. 
ich fühle mich mitverantwortlich, die gesellschaft für dieses tabuthema zu sensibilisieren. es kommt häufiger vor, als man meint. 
manchmal schäme ich mich, dass mich das auch heute noch oft belastet u. verfolgt- auch wenn mir meistens bewusst ist: solche ereignisse beeinflussen die psyche eines menschen zwangsläufig langfristig, sodass man oft ein leben lang (immer wieder)damit „kämpfen“ muss-aber auch darf. 
#sexuellermissbrauch #missbrauch #ptbs #depressionen #trauma #angst #kämpfer #verarbeitung #ama #aufklärung #metoo #portrait #realtalk #projekteinzigartich

text:
an essential read. clarissa pinkola estés, the women who run with the wolves. 'while much psychology emphasises the familial causes of angst in humans, the cultural component carries as much weight, for culture is the family if the family. if the family of the family has various sicknesses, then all families within that culture will have to struggle with the same malaises. in my heritage, there is a saying, 'cultura cura', culture cures. if the culture is a healer, the families learn how to heal; they will struggle less, be more reparative, far less wounding, far more graceful and loving. in a culture where the predator rules, all new life needing to be born, all old life needing to be gone, is unable to move and the soul-lives of its citizenry are paralysed with both fear and spiritual famine.' this quote actually jumped out at the time of dr christine blasey ford's courageous testimony. now we're thinking about all those who are doing the work of making culture that cures. people like @alokvmenon and @travisalabanza and @leopardprintelephant who share the experience of being gender non-conforming and non-binary, giving inspiration and hope and beauty to so many; organisations like @rapecrisisscotland who create a save haven for survivors of abuse; and further afield, cultural leaders like @jadapinkettsmith @busyphilipps and @lavernecox who inspire us with their womanhood every damn day. 
#thewomenwhorunwithwolves #feminist #intersectionalfeminism #transisbeautiful #translivesmatter #believewomen #metoo #timesup #representationmatters

text:
stringers, a burnt child they say dreads fire. however, this is not always the case as this idiom does not necessarily cover the bahaviours of some individuals.

rewind to 1977, colleen stan was kidnapped by a couple, cameron hooker and his wife janice and forced to live in a wooden restraining box underneath their bed. stan was forced by her captives to live life as some form of domestic/sex slave for about 7years; she was abused physically and sexually during her period of captivity.

even though she was allowed to socialize with cameron’s wife, janice and even visit her mother, she still continued to live in the box and did not attempt to escape or even reach out for help.

eventually, she was freed by janice, who asked stan to not disclose her abuse as janice was attempting to reform cameron. stan remained silent until janice finally decided to turn cameron over to the police. this is a very famous example of the infamous condition called stockholm syndrome.
stockholm syndrome is a condition where a captive or victim of abuse, begins to psychologically or even emphatically bond with his/her captor or abuser.

stockholm syndrome is more involved in the sustenance of abusive relationships than most people know. leaving any relationship (abusive or not) is never easy; making up your mind to leave someone who you’ve shared so much with in so long a time is not an easy fit. but then, there are extreme cases where everyone else sees the life threatening danger, so does the victim, but he/she decides to keep going back after every beat down and maltreatment.
studies show that abuse (whether emotional or physical), blended with moments of kindness can bond some victims to their abusers even more than consistent good treatment can. in most abusive relationships, especially emotionally abusive ones, the victim has chances to leave and escape but they do not. 
it might also interest you to know that ‘belle’ from ‘beauty and the beast’ is considered by many to be a victim of stockholm syndrome. 
click link in bio or https://wp.me/p8iyek-6bu for full story

text:
read the caption

it's been almost a month since the #metoo storm took a full swing all over the social media and there hasn't been any justice given to these victims. have they?? i don't think so. the victims have been tortured in all possible ways and they have been physically and emotionally weak, that they have shut themselves down from everyone and pushed to the verge of ending their lives. indeed, some have ended their lives. and the survivors are living their lives like a living dead. i'm not exaggerating anything here. no matter how much support we give them, how much we listen to them, the horrific experiences that they had gone through can never be forgotten or understood by us. and if they forget, the wound pricks every time, they read about yet another incident. it is like the worst nightmare coming to reality. i appreciate everyone of us supporting, listening and standing by the sides of these victims and helping them to raise their voice against their perpetrators. it takes immense courage for these women to open up after everything that they have been through and there comes the group of men and to my surprise women slut shaming them. what does it take for you people to empathize for a fellow human? if you are not going to be of any help, then don't just say anything. they have already been tortured in and out and these group ask insensitive questions and claims like, "why didn't you say then?; what took you so long? ; what is your motive? ; oh, she is just seeking attention; what is your caste?" wait. what? yeah, you read it right. caste. like it matters so much to raise one's voice for justice. these questions sounds like, "this is what happens in this country, that's nothing new. they are doing what have to do and let's see what you can do about it" with a huge evil grin on the face. and i'm so ashamed to say but this is what is happening in this country. #metoo storm hit every social media platforms and there have been endless cases against several personalities from different walks of life. alright, now these slut shaming group would say, "these victims are hiding behind the smart screens, they are alleging anonymously for whatsoever reasons"

text_retweet:
reposting this image because it is so, so important.
•
the past few days i found myself getting more and more upset at my friend because she wasn't communicating with me. i was angry because she wasn't being honest with me, and i almost lashed out at her.
•
honestly, i was hurt. but i remembered statements about what i can control. i can't control what she does or what she shares with me, but i can control how i respond to her and how i handle my frustrations.
•
the hardest lesson i've learned is to let go. the number of things i can control is incredibly small when compared to things  out of my control. this weekend, i challenge everyone to recognize one thing you can't control, and let go. - diane
•

text:
just a reminder that you have until december 31st to submit your stories for my #metoo: a collection of true story crimes against women.
get your stories in! be heard! help others know that they are not alone.
.
my latest project is called “#metoo: a collection of true story crimes against women.”
i am still collecting stories. submissions will be accepted until december 31, 2018.
if you have a story that you would like to include email me at mchillstromauthor@yahoo.com.
all stories will be listed as anonymous submissions.
the types of stories i am looking for include personal experiences of:
-sexual harassment -rape/assault -sexual, emotional, or physical abuse
-stalking
-gender discrimination
-i will accept other topics if they fit in with the theme as well.
through writing my own stories i have found peace and strength.
i hope others will find this as well along with the knowledge that they are not alone.
proceeds from the sales of this collection will be donated to help sexual assault survivors.
.
.

text:
this is an image of a hindu goddess whose name means "never not broken" she derives her powers from being broken and reminds us that we, too, can find power in the broken places. when we’re broken the stories, narratives, and expectations that silently guide us no longer apply. we can become whole again, in a new way. we can find a new flow, and we have an opportunity to transform and be transformed. akhilanda rides a crocodile — she literally rides her fears. 
why are we telling you this? because later this month we're hosting a healing community gathering around the kavanaugh hearings, led by local psychotherapist emily swanson. if the recent hearings left you feeling vulnerable, or angry, or triggered, or something else entirely different, but with nowhere to turn, you are welcome to come by. 
please register for a spot on our website as spaces are limited.

#postkavanaughearingstherapy #metoo #healingspaces #therapy #womensupportingwomen

thank god i had extra top in the bag.
i quickly changed and took some pictures. 
we just have to keep moving on in life. no holding back.

together we can change our community a person at a time.

text:
4- 🇺🇸etats-unis: madame lena headey, témoignage pour le magazine marie claire.•
•
la comédienne lena headey, interprète de cersei lannister dans "game of thrones", a révélé dans une série de tweets postés le 17 octobre 2017 faire également partie des victimes d’harvey weinstein.•
•
par deux fois, le producteur a tenté de soumettre l’actrice à ses désirs. la première fois en 2005, au cours du festival du film de venise. le réalisateur aurait proposé une balade à l’actrice, qui aurait décliné en riant la proposition. « j'ai dit quelque chose comme ‘voyons, ce serait comme embrasser mon père, allons prendre un verre et rejoindre les autres’ ». il ne s’est pourtant pas arrêté là.•
•
l’actrice recroise harvey weinstein quelque temps plus tard, à los angeles. elle explique alors que le producteur aurait voulu lui montrer un scénario se trouvant dans sa chambre. alertée par une sorte d'instinct de survie, la comédienne lui aurait fait immédiatement comprendre qu’elle n’était pas intéressée.•
•
"on est sorti de l'ascenseur et avons atteint sa chambre. sa main était dans mon dos, il me forçait à avancer, sans un mot. je me sentais tellement impuissante. ii a essayé d'ouvrir la porte avec sa carte mais ça n'a pas marché et il s'est vraiment mis en colère. il m'a raccompagnée à l'ascenseur, à travers tout l'hôtel et jusqu'au voiturier, en m'attrapant et me tenant fermement par le bras. il a payé pour ma voiture et m'a murmuré à l'oreille : 'ne raconte ça à personne, pas à ton manager, pas à ton agent.' je suis montée dans ma voiture et j'ai pleuré."•
•
le mouvement #metoo depuis l’affaire wenstein a permis à de nombreuses femmes de faire entendre leur parole dans ce pays et de faire savoir qu’elles avaient été victimes de harcèlements et d’agressions sexuels.•
•
-aux etats-unis, 700 000 femmes sont violées ou victimes d’autres formes d’agressions sexuelles chaque année. 14,8% de ces femmes ont moins de 17 ans. -dans le monde, jusqu’à 50 % des agressions sexuelles sont commises à l’encontre de jeunes filles de moins de 16 ans. on estime que 150 millions de filles de moins de 18 ans ont subi une forme de violence sexuelle ou une autre, rien qu'en 2002.•
•
@iamlenaheadey

text:
link in bio for complete video. freddie mercury is one of my favorite singers. he is a man who sang with the essence of his true creativity, passion and sensuality. he quotes, “i won't be a rock star. i will be a legend,” and so he is!  today, #bohemianrhapsodymovie movie is being released, and in honor of him, i decided to arrange an acoustic mash-up version of my favorite queen/bowie song, “under pressure” and “i want to break free.” as a child, i didn’t really understand it’s meaning–i just felt something. all these years later, the message is just as powerful and important - if not even more so today to me, it’s about the struggle we all face to transcend the pressure of a dualistic world obsessed with perfection and to find the love within, that heals us all. it’s about being true to who we are and not letting the weight of “the world” destroy us. it can be about so many things to so many people. i just hope the message touches your heart in some way, as it did mine. please share with those who might need a lift.

text: happy 1 year sober to me :p i honestly can't believe it's been a year already. some may not think it's a big deal but it is to me. after smoking pot everyday for almost 6 years i'm proud that i don't even think about it or want it anymore. 6 years ago i was dealing with the mental after effects of sexual assault and used alcohol and pot to try to forget. i've come a long way since then and am so glad that i've dealt with all of those negative feelings and understand that it wasn't my fault. if you are struggling, there's always a way out. just gotta start talking about it and ask for help. #sober #1yearsober #metoo #happy #youcandoittoo #noshame #endthestigma

text:
📚 lecture terminée 📚
-----
tu t'appelais maria schneider de vanessa schneider, un document qui fait partie de la sélection du #grandprixdeslectriceselle2019
-----
l'histoire : vanessa schneider raconte avec pudeur, tendresse et réalisme l'histoire de sa cousine maria que vingt ans séparent.
cette cousine, elle l'a régulièrement vu chez elle enfant. elle l'a connu triste. elle l'a connu joyeuse. elle l'a connu droguée. elle l'a connu en manque. elle l'a surtout connu mal aimée. d'abord par ses parents.  puis par le milieu du cinéma. enfin par le public.
marie schneider, cette jeune fille qui se rêvait actrice et qu'un rôle maudit a brisé à tout jamais : celui de jeanne dans le dernier tango à paris.
c'est dans ce film qu'une scène non écrite dans le scénario original et d'une extrême violence pour elle, scellera son avenir. un traumatisme qui ne sera jamais effacé par un rôle qui l'aura détruite et pour lequel elle sera marquée au fer rouge tout au long de sa carrière et de sa vie.
-----
mon avis : avant d'ouvrir ce livre, le nom de maria schneider ne me disait rien. il ne me parlait pas.
en refermant ce livre, j'ai eu l'impression de quitter une petite soeur, à l'histoire touchante, émouvante. une petite soeur que j'ai eu envie d'épauler, de soutenir. une petite soeur que j'ai eu envie de prendre dans mes bras pour la rassurer et lui dire que tout irait bien.
-----
a l'ère du mouvement #metoo, ce document a une résonance toute particulière et mérite d'être lu.
-----
a qui l'offrir : aux passionnés de cinéma 📽
-----

text:
in burkas, and smiles, these 13-16 year olds became one with the ocean and changed my life forever. .

these girls have never surfed. some can’t swim. i had the honor of teaching them to surf as part of @discoversoneva sustainable surf program’s community outreach (see my last two video posts)
🌊
big thanks to @saltysun__ and everyone at #sonevafushi who organized this adventure and for your commitment to supporting waves of change for women in the maldives.
.
book your stay at @discoversoneva and become part of the change! .
🏄‍♀️ ***in some cultures these would not be considered a full burka but this is what the women told me to call them:) .
📷 @hisarahlee

why are men checking out of relationships?⠀

text:
lullaby - by leila slimani
.
.
—— available on our website
.
——- leïla slimani: ‘everyone asks me, “why do you choose such subversive or shocking themes?”’ a life in ...
leïla slimani on her shocking bestseller, lullaby: 'who can really say they know their nanny?'
her murderous nanny thriller gripped france, winning its top literary prize and the attention of president macron. with lullaby now out in english, the author shares her thoughts on motherhood, #metoo and being a muslim in france
——-
the book description: “the baby is dead. it only took a few seconds,” so begins lullaby. first we had the murderous perfect wife, gone girl, in 2012, then the murderous perfect husband, the girl on the train, in 2015, and now the murderous “perfect nanny” – the us title for the goncourt-winning french bestseller, published in the states and the uk this month. lullaby is ménage à trois as domestic noir; the relationship, as intimate and intense as any affair, between a couple and their nanny. it was “like love at first sight”, says myriam, the mother, of their first meeting. until, like a “wounded lover”, the nanny stabs the two children in the bath, before slitting her own throat. this is not a spoiler: it’s all there in the devastating opening pages.
.
.
——-

text:
the impact of trauma can be intense and long lasting. healing from trauma may mean intensive and long-term treatment, as the impact trauma has on memory, the body, and the nervous system, can be profound⠀
💜⠀
trauma memories have a big impact on survivors’ explicit and implicit memory. trauma can shut down parts of memory, can cause survivors to be triggered without explanation, and can change patterns in procedural memory⠀
💜⠀
all of these memory related shifts can lead to increased dissociation, and unwanted somatic experiences that may be unexplained. the body may feel pain or numbness as a response to a trauma trigger, and since the survivor’s brain is off line (during dissociation) they may lack the context for what is happening. here, the mind, body, and nervous system are trapped in the trauma memory ⠀
💜⠀
in these moments, it often feels like your body is betraying you, and you may feel increased distress which could make way for feelings of guilt or shame⠀
💜⠀
this process may be circular, and it may take trauma-informed therapy (and other trauma-informed treatments) to get the mind, body, and nervous system, all on the same page. don’t give up on your healing, with increased awareness and self-acceptance, you will learn to cope with your trauma in ways that are in service of your healing 💜⠀
.⠀
.⠀
.⠀
.⠀

text:
im not one to get political, partly cause there’s a lot i do not understand when it comes to politics and government… but during this current administration, i am constantly (almost daily) shocked and saddened by the things being said and done by our so-called leader. but, we always have to try and find a positive in everything, and i always try make to every experience or event a ‘lesson learned’ …. in september, when the kavanaugh hearings were going on, i tried in my best way, to explain to my girls what was going on… before, during and after…the trials and especially when dr #christineblaseyford was on the stand…. and it was a good time to explain boundaries , consent and respect … when the decision was made to appoint kavanaugh, i was in disbelief, and saddened to say the least… but again, learning experience, and i was very glad that the lines of communication were opened and my girls and i were able to touch on the subject. it also opened up the conversation for me to tell them, things like this should not happen, and women need to be represented in all areas, but especially government. the lawmakers and law enforcers should represent the people, all people, not just a certain gender or color. sometimes i wonder and think if they ‘get it’…. or if it just sounds like ‘blahblahblah’ when i talk… lol

well, this week was spirit week at gracie’s school @kippsol … and today was ‘support your cause’ day… assignment: ‘advocate for yourself and support what you stand for and believe…’… so gracie said ‘how about dr ford …’ so i proudly  present to you, my love, my flaquita, my tutu…. as dr. christine blasey ford (sorry we didn’t get a wig… lol)… but ayyyy my gracie makes me so proud!! i think
she gets it!! cause dr. ford is a true hero!! and despite the trauma she suffered, her courage to come forward and speak the #truth, none of it was in vain.... there’s a whole new generation of young girls watching... learning... and i hope, one day will #takeaction ... #changetheworld #advocate #believewomen #webelieve #timesup #metoo #speakup #thefutureisfemale  @kippsol @kippschools #wecandoit #sisepuede #ibelievechristineblaseyford #@kipplapublicschools @mazilove27

text:
in wenigen tagen stehen die midterm-wahlen in den usa vor der tür. ich habe einige eindrücke aus meiner usa-reise niedergeschrieben und was für die usa mit diesen wahlen auf dem spiel steht.

was mir großen mut macht, ist die zahl der frauen, die sich auf ein politisches amt bewerben. nach #metoo und der kavanaugh-entscheidung haben sich hunderte frauen überlegt, für das repräsentantenhaus anzutreten, dutzende wollen senatorin werden oder bleiben. und natürlich sind die meisten kandidatinnen demokratinnen!

jetzt schaue ich gebannt nach amerika, drücke den demokraten und vor allem den vielen kandidatinnen die daumen, damit donald trump besser kontrolliert werden kann, gesetze aus der konservativen agenda der republikaner verhindert werden können und ein politikwechsel, vor allem mit mehr frauen in der politik, eingeläutet werden kann!

link dazu —>bio! 
#usa #midtermelections #democrats 
#europe #empowerment #europasindwir

text:
over decades of ministry i’ve counseled women who have dealt with various forms of sexual harassment. with the recent #metoo movement, the topic has become big news, and it is starting to get the attention it deserves.

let’s lay all of the cards out on the table. sexual harassment is one of those insidious evils that surround us. it lurks in the background and we don’t really pay much attention to it until it directly affects us in some way.

as women, we are often told we need to “move past” any “uncomfortable” situations we’ve experienced. as in the situation made us uncomfortable, but that’s the extent of it, giving the impression the woman is overreacting. all too often, sexual harassment is swept under the rug, or dealt with quietly so the situation just goes away.

i focus on two areas of this important topic in my newest blog post. first, i look a little closer at sexual harassment: what it is, who it affects, and what kind of damage it causes. then i look at the steps someone who is sexually harassed can take to find healing and how we can help.

•⠀
(free) 5 abuse medihealing® sessions: tinyurl.com/abuse-freedom2⠀
• ⠀
teal's book: tealswan.com/loneliness⠀
• ⠀
as we prepare to launch our abuse series at the top of 2019, the timing couldn’t have been better for me to have sat down with renowned speaker and author, teal swan, to discuss her personal upbringing with abuse and how we all experience it based upon her perspective on loneliness.⠀
⠀
if we look at society, we see trauma everywhere—from improper weaning of babies to the ravages of war. without a doubt, it has become a societal epidemic yet we’ve somehow succumbed to the enormity of its ubiquity that it’s almost deemed “normal.” it has unfortunately widened the chasm of perceived separation into deep loneliness that affects millions in spite of billions in population on planet earth.⠀
⠀
teal clarifies that these are all essentially fragments of perception and identities we’ve created in order to survive. and the task, at hand, is to have all of society engage in commitment to understand each other and ultimately ourselves. she further specifies there is a need for genuine connection because we are a group species, and it is in our basic biology to be with and be in mutual understanding of one another.⠀ ⠀
listen in to this episode to hear teal’s take on loneliness and how you can learn more from her latest book, the anatomy of loneliness.⠀
•⠀

text: "you were just a baby when #metoo entered our national consciousness last october and immediately become a cultural touchstone. at 18 months old, your most pressing concerns were sesame street, grilled cheese, and fire trucks. you won’t remember how it felt to watch those floodgates break and see the collective pain that women have carried in silence for so long spill out into the open. you won’t recall the distinct blend of pride and anguish as woman after woman reached into the darkest corners of their souls and pulled out their secrets to lay bare, many for the first time."head on over to our blog to read the rest of my letter to my daughter on the me too movement

text_retweet:
because i am trying really to alter how i look at the experience myself. guess it's a long journey for me to achieve it but i do believe cbt can be extremely helpful. #sexualharassment
#ptsdrecovery
#ptsd #sexualabuse #letustalk #opendialogue #metoo #metooindia #survivor #staystrong 
#repost from @shewillsurvivedotcom 
one thing that really helped me put my past behind me is cbt (cognitive behavioural therapy). i learned that you can alter your experience by how you frame and think about what you've been through. you can actually change how you interpret and react to what you've been through. you can assess what happened and learn to see things differently. this in turn starts to impact how you handle your past and how you see things going forward. it eventually gets easier to accept, to learn from, to talk about and to grow from what happened. 
you can eventually go from victim to survivor 
on that note, i'm sending out [virtual] positive vibes to all my fellow survivors  #positive #motivation #survival #thinkpositive #inspiration #shewillsurvive #quote #dvawareness #cbt #gethelp #theotherside #stopabuse #eradicaterape #startingover #empowerwomen #speakout #breakthestigma #mentalhealth

there's so much (saddening) talk in my world about women - our restricted rights, our bodies as battlegrounds, the abuse and harassment we've experienced at work, the injustice of un-equal pay, the millions of us who have said #metoo in the past year... .
yet these conversation are critical if we're going to ensure the next generation doesn't have to go thru what we have. .
.
at the same time, nothing will change unless men change too. we cant do it alone. that's why this post is about the incredible men in my life, and how they show up in the world. today, the work that my friend and mentor @saschaflavor has been doing with @_evryman_ was featured on national tv; it felt so good to see @jiivy front and center; what he said about redefining masculinity, intimacy and dismantling machismo is exactly what's needed to move forward .
.
earlier in the morning, my incredible friend @mjrothman sent me this image of him and our friend @cossmarte. good men who are giving, caring, compassionate entrepreneurs who seamlessly blend being successful with being open-hearted, honest and caring. coss came home from prison and built a program that provides jobs to the formerly incarcerated, and fitness to hundreds of people a day. mike doenst talk about it much, but he's literally traversed one end of the country to the other on a bike to raise money for people impacted by mass incarceration . .
.
i firmly believe men like the ones im lucky enough to love, are going to lead us forward. they do it by being committed to facing their own demons, going into their own pain, connecting to their bodies, and being open with each other. that in turn redefines how they show up at work, in relationships with their partners, and as friends . .
.
grateful to know you, grateful to love you and grateful for your collective leadership

text:
“there is so much evidence. this is the era of the #metoo movement, but even before that there is so much evidence if we are willing to pay attention; that these traditional ways that women are vulnerable to being taken advantage of across a broad spectrum. we have known that many many women are vulnerable and have been victimized in some ways at some points in our lives – i am one of those women. so it’s a difficult time to be reminded of how prevalent it is and seeing the system responding in ways that are very apparently self-protective of the nominee, just to see that level of defensiveness and unwillingness perhaps to be open to what may be known is its own shocking revelation.” – rhonda magee (@rvmagee)

this time on the bhnn guest podcast, @francescamaxime sits down for a conversation with professor rhonda v. magee about bringing mindfulness to systemic injustice.

link in our bio!

rhonda v. magee is professor of law at the university of san francisco and is an internationally-recognized thought and practice leader on integrating mindfulness into higher education, law and social justice.

this conversation was recorded on september 26th, 2018 – nearly four weeks into what has become a historical supreme court judicial appointment and confirmation hearing of #brettkavanaugh. this hearing became a national conversation as focus quickly turned to multiple accusations from women in kavanaugh’s early adulthood who claim to have a witness to and victims of sexual abuse by kavanaugh. francesca and rhona look at the bigger lessons to take from the hearing and what role contemplative practices play in healing systemic abuse.

this podcast is brought to you by the generosity of @1440multiversity – california’s newest retreat destination which hosts a faculty of thought leaders in fields including mindfulness, neuroscience, relationships, the creative arts, and more.

join krishna das and sharon salzberg november 16 – 18, 2018 for an immersive and in-depth weekend at 1440 multiversity on how to create a spacious balance of mind that will nurture a more direct, experiential relationship with love of all kinds.

text:
can you love me anyways?

can you love me despite my wounds and scars and the messiness i might bring with me? can you see my potential and value under the cracks and mud that might cake my beauty at times? can you show me love when i am unloving towards you, because i'm triggered and i dont feel safe? can you journey with me on this rollercoaster that we call life?

most importantly, can you love you? because that needs to come first before you can ever love me anyways.

still a queen 👑✊.
.
.
.

text:
‘colours of light’
light dazzles my eyes,
as the sparks emitted 
come in every conceivable 
shape, colour and size:
they fill up the staid autumn sky,
setting my heart a flutter 
like all those butterflies - daylong
hovering around garden paths,
sucking nectar from
flowers of every colour and form,
that are now in full bloom 
amidst the chalets and barns 
of my childhood fantasies 
from all the classic novels 
i’d keep my head buried in,
that would take me to another world,
to hide from the reality of my situations.

these diwali shards of brilliant light
now ignite my mind’s eye,
setting my thoughts racing wild
to when i was a child of nine
and sorely afraid of the dark.
such that, i’d close my eyes and run
to the light switch boards on the far wall,
of my boarding school dormitory hall,
if i came up to my locker out of time —
feeling my way with my hands, 
panicking but managing not to fall,
like playing blind-man’s-buff with my fears,
wherein i was to extricate myself from them
so i couldn’t lose my sense of self ever again —
in the flurry of adult life, when at work 
i’d fight for my rights and my self esteem,
not act a victim in the circumstances:
when it’d take a turn into a dark alley of men
trying to overpower me with their clout,
throwing me overboard many a times
but always providing me from my own torch —
strong beams of logical reasoning and light,
to guide my confident and unique strides.

time's up is a movement against sexual harassment and was founded on january 1, 2018, by hollywood celebrities in response to the weinstein effect and #metoo. in november 2017, the alianza nacional de campesinas wrote a letter of solidarity to the hollywood women involved in exposing the sexual abuse  allegations against harvey weinstein. the letter, published in time, described experiences of assult and harasment among female farmworkers. the letter stated that it was written on behalf of the approximately 700,000 female farmworkers in the united states and it's not just the united states but the whole world. we must stand together against rape, harasment, and sexual abuse. don't let that happen to you, don't let that happen to anyone. ✊💪👸

la peli pasó sin mucha pena ni gloria, pero merece ser vista.

text:
g witness october 
a review of the world in 57’ .
"it's been a year of shocking testimonies." - comments about the #metoo movement
.
october marks one year since the creation of #metoo. a once small and unspoken topic has grown exponentially and this has formed the foundation of the fempowerment movement, which will gain traction for years to come. it gave people a voice, a platform to stand on and has united millions of victims. rihanna took a stand against racism in the nfl by refusing to perform in the prestigious half time show. ms meaza ashanafi has made history by becoming the first female president of ethiopia, which is set to inspire a new generation of female political leaders.
.
kanye west and donald trump stole the show in the us by demonstrating to the world how two people with huge egos interact. as the public goes to the voting stations this month, 
the president should aim to be on his best behaviour as he seeks to garner the votes of the american people.
.
we are deeply saddened by the horrific killings at the pittsburgh synagogue, with a gunman taking the lives of 11 people. the sporting world was stunned as vichai srivaddhanaprabha tragically passed away in a freak helicopter accident. south africa lost a legend as hhp was found dead in his home. his music, charm and passion will be sorely missed.
.
back home, south africa’s banking and government sectors were under the spotlight as the vbs scandal was brought to light. key players have had to answer uncomfortable questions about millions of missing rands. it will be interesting to see if newly elected financial minister mr tito mboweni will address this crisis.
.
as the end of the year is closing in, we need to prepare ourselves for more scandals, more ringside brawls and of course more people standing together for a cause.
.

text:
our #freestyle artist for the day is nneka uzoma gigi!
.
a contemporary visual artist, doctorial student and educator.
she is a multi talented artist, who specializes in paintings for print, body painting, haircrafts and sculpting.
.
.
today we feature an art sculpture piece, the very first of its kind called "amaka".
.
in her words:
a woman doesn't have to provide access to her body as proof she likes you.
.
.
my 1st sculpture ever, amaka, was created to shed light on the rape laws in nigeria while encouraging others to understand their own state laws regarding rape + sexual assault .
.
.
it was also a therapeutic exercise to discuss surviving my own rape from an emotional aspect all these years later...
.
.
to know more about gigi
instagram: @nnekagigi
website: www.nnekagigi.com
.
you can also read more about her on our website: http://www.thesparkng.com/contemporary-visual-art-nneka/ or see #linkinbio
.

text:
men are socialized to be strong, tough, unemotional, and brave. when little boys cry, they are told to “buck up.” when they express emotional distress, they are told to “be a man.” this societal repression of male emotionality results in the troubling construct known as toxic masculinity.
•
#toxicmasculinity has many negative effects, including the perpetuation of the gender wage gap, sexual harassment, and intimate partner violence. another important ramification is the increased stigma around mental illness and seeking mental health services in those identifying as male.
•
the @goodmenproject defines toxic masculinity as follows: toxic masculinity is a narrow and repressive description of manhood, designating manhood as defined by violence, sex, status and aggression. it’s the cultural ideal of manliness, where strength is everything while emotions are a weakness; where sex and brutality are yardsticks by which men are measured, while supposedly “feminine” traits—which can range from emotional vulnerability to simply not being hypersexual—are the means by which your status as “man” can be taken away.
•
the idea that emotional vulnerability detracts from one’s status as a man is incredibly problematic for male mental health. in many cases, it results in an emotional style similar to a clinical syndrome known as alexithymia. those with alexithymia “have difficulty describing their feelings, their cognitive style is concrete and reality-based, and they have impoverished emotional and fantasy lives” (taylor et al., 1985).
•
one study even found that men reporting greater gender role conflict endorsed greater levels of alexithymia and fear of intimacy (fischer & good, 1997). aside from the societal impacts of making men feel uncomfortable seeking mental health care, this has implications for those who do go to psychotherapy, which requires clients to connect with their thoughts and feelings in order to understand their psychiatric symptoms and interpersonal patterns.
•
join us in supporting @themightysite in helping to reduce the stigma of mental illness and emotional expression in men by encouraging men to share their feelings with one another #itsokman

text:
#metoo பிரச்சனைக்கு தென்னிந்திய நடிகர் சங்கம் குழு அமைப்பு ￼

கேளிக்கை சினிமா

#metoo பிரச்சனைக்கு தென்னிந்திய நடிகர் சங்கம் குழு அமைப்பு

posted on october 31, 2018 authorஸ்பெல்கோcomment(0)  engaged 405

பகிர்வுக்கு

9shares

share

tweet

pin

linkedin

google+

#metoo என்ற இயக்கம் மூலம் பெண்கள் தங்களுக்கு பணியிடங்களிலோ, வெளியிலோ நிகழ்ந்த பாலியல் தொந்தரவுகளை வெளிப்படுத்தி வருகிறார்கள். உலகம் முழுக்க பிரபலமான இந்த மீடூ இயக்கம், தமிழ்நாட்டிலும் நீண்ட நாட்களாக பேசப்பட்டு வருகிறது. இதில் திரைத்துறையை சார்ந்தவர்களே அதிகம் குற்றச்சாட்டிற்க்கு ஆளானவர்கள். #metoo சர்ச்சை தொடர்பாக ஆலோசிக்க, தென்னிந்திய நடிகர் சங்கம் சார்பில், தலைவர் நாசர் தலைமையில் செயற்குழுக் கூட்டம் நடைபெற்றது. பின்னர், செய்தியாளர்களை சந்தித்த நிர்வாகிகள், “திரைத்துறையில் பணியாற்றும் பெண்களின் பாதுகாப்பை உறுதி செய்யும் சட்டங்கள் ஏற்கனவே தென்னிந்திய நடிகர் சங்க விதிகளில் இடம்பெற்றுள்ளன.

எனினும், நடிகர் சங்கத்தின் சுயமரியாதையை காப்பாற்றும் விதமாக, நீதிமன்ற வழிகாட்டுதலன் படி, விசாகா கமிட்டி அடிப்படையில் ஒரு பெரும் குழு அமைக்கப்படும். பெரும்பான்மையாக பெண்கள் அங்கம் வகிக்கும் அந்த குழுவில், மனநல மருத்துவரும் இடம்பெறுவார். ஆண்கள், பெண்கள் என வேறுபாடின்றி, பிரச்னைகளை பொதுவாக பேசும் தளமாக அது இயங்கும். திரைத்துறையில் பணியிடங்களில் ஏற்படும் பிரச்னைகளுக்கு உடண்டியாக தீர்வு காணு வகையில் இந்த குழுவின் செயல்பாடுகள் அமையும். இதற்கு தமிழ் திரைப்பட தயாரிப்பாளர்கள் சங்கம் தலைமையில், தென்னிந்திய நடிகர் சங்கம், தென்னிந்திய திரைப்பட தொழிலாளர்கள் சம்மேளனம், இயக்குநர்கள் சங்கம் உள்ளிட்ட உயர்மட்ட குழு ஒன்றை அமைக்கவும் பரிந்துரை செய்கிறது” என தென்னிந்திய நடிகர் சங்க தலைவர் நாசர் தெரிவித்தார். #nassar#south indian artistes association#vishal#தென்னிந்திய நடிகர் சங்கம்#நாசர்#விசாகா#விசாகா#குழு

posted on october 31, 2018 authorஸ்பெல்கோcomment(0)  engaged 405

 என்ற இயக்கம் மூலம் பெண்கள் தங்களுக்கு பணியிடங்களிலோ, வெளியிலோ நிகழ்ந்த பாலியல் தொந்தரவுகளை வெளிப்படுத்தி வருகிறார்கள். உலகம் முழுக்க பிரபலமான இந்த மீடூ இயக்கம், தமிழ்நாட்டிலும் நீண்ட நாட்களாக பேசப்பட்டு வருகிறது. இதில் திரைத்துறையை சார்ந்தவர்களே அதிகம் குற்றச்சாட்டிற்க்கு ஆளானவர்கள்.  சர்ச்சை தொடர்பாக ஆலோசிக்க, தென்னிந்திய நடிகர் சங்கம் சார்பில், தலைவர் நாசர் தலைமையில் செயற்குழுக் கூட்டம் நடைபெற்றது. பின்னர், செய்தியாளர்களை சந்தித்த நிர்வாகிகள், “திரைத்துறையில் பணியாற்றும் பெண்களின் பாதுகாப்பை உறுதி செய்யும் சட்டங்கள் ஏற்கனவே தென்னிந்திய நடிகர் சங்க விதிகளில் இடம்பெற்றுள்ளன.

எனினும், நடிகர் சங்கத்தின் சுயமரியாதையை காப்பாற்றும் விதமாக, நீதிமன்ற வழிகாட்டுதலன் படி, விசாகா கமிட்டி அடிப்படையில் ஒரு பெரும் குழு அமைக்கப்படும். பெரும்பான்மையாக பெண்கள் அங்கம் வகிக்கும் அந்த குழுவில், மனநல மருத்துவரும் இடம்பெறுவார். ஆண்கள், பெண்கள் என வேறுபாடின்றி, பிரச்னைகளை பொதுவாக பேசும் தளமாக அது இயங்கும். திரைத்துறையில் பணியிடங்களில் ஏற்படும் பிரச்னைகளுக்கு உடண்டியாக தீர்வு காணு வகையில் இந்த குழுவின் செயல்பாடுகள் அமையும். இதற்கு தமிழ் திரைப்பட தயாரிப்பாளர்கள் சங்கம் தலைமையில், தென்னிந்திய நடிகர் சங்கம், தென்னிந்திய திரைப்பட தொழிலாளர்கள் சம்மேளனம், இயக்குநர்கள் சங்கம் உள்ளிட்ட உயர்மட்ட குழு ஒன்றை அமைக்கவும் பரிந்துரை செய்கிறது” என தென்னிந்திய நடிகர் சங்க தலைவர் நாசர் தெரிவித்தார்.  indian aistes association நடிகர் சங்கம்ாசர்ிசாகாிசாகாுழு
stop_filter_tweet: பிரச்சனைக்கு தென்னிந்திய நடிகர் சங்கம் குழு அமைப்பு ￼ கேளிக்கை சினிமா பிரச்சனைக்கு தென்னிந்திய நடிகர் சங்கம் குழு அமைப்பு posted october 31 , 2018 authorஸ்பெல்கோcomment ( 0 ) engaged 405 பகிர்வுக்கு 9shares share tweet pin linkedin google+ என்ற இயக்கம் மூலம் பெண்கள் தங்களுக்கு பணியிடங்களிலோ , வெளியிலோ நிகழ்ந்த பாலியல் தொந்தரவுகளை வெளிப்படுத்தி வருகிறார்கள் . உலகம் முழுக்க பிரபலமான இந்த மீடூ இயக்கம் , தமிழ்நாட்டிலும் நீண்ட நாட்களாக பேசப்பட்டு வருகிறது . இதில் திரைத்துறையை சார்ந்தவர்களே அதிகம் குற்றச்சாட்டிற்க்கு ஆளானவர்கள் . சர்ச்சை தொடர்பாக ஆலோசிக்க , தென்னிந்திய நடிகர் சங்கம் சார்பில் , தலைவர் நாசர் தலைமையில் செயற்குழுக் கூட்டம் நடைபெற்றது . பின்னர் , செய்தியாளர்களை சந்தித்த நிர்வாகிகள் , “ திரைத்துறையில் பணியாற்றும் பெண்களின் பாதுகாப்பை உறுதி செய்யும் சட்டங்கள் ஏற்கனவே தென்னிந்திய நடிகர் சங்க விதிகளில் இடம்பெற்றுள்ளன . எனினும் , நடிகர் சங்கத்தின் சுயமரியாதையை காப்பாற்றும் விதமாக , நீதிமன்ற வழிகாட்டுதலன் படி , விசாகா கமிட்டி அடிப்படையில் ஒரு பெரும் குழு அமைக்கப்படும் . பெரும்பான்மையாக பெண்கள் அங்கம் வகிக்கும் அந்த குழுவில் , மனநல மருத்துவரும் இடம்பெறுவார் . ஆண்கள் , பெண்கள் என வேறுபாடின்றி , பிரச்னைகளை பொதுவாக பேசும் தளமாக அது இயங்கும் . திரைத்துறையில் பணியிடங்களில் ஏற்படும் பிரச்னைகளுக்கு உடண்டியாக தீர்வு காணு வகையில் இந்த குழுவின் செயல்பாடுகள் அமையும் . இதற்கு தமிழ் திரைப்பட தயாரிப்பாளர்கள் சங்கம் தலைமையில் , தென்னிந்திய நடிகர் சங்கம் , தென்னிந்திய திரைப்பட தொழிலாளர்கள் சம்மேளனம் , இயக்குநர்கள் சங்கம் உள்ளிட்ட உயர்மட்ட குழு ஒன்றை அமைக்கவும் பரிந்துரை செய்கிறது ” என தென்னிந்திய நடிகர் சங்க தலைவர் நாசர் தெரிவித்தார் . indian aistes association நடிகர் சங்கம்ாசர்ிசாகாிசாகாுழு
